ascents.comment: Another really good climb I have never read the description for, but may seriously warm up here instead of slow dance area. Thank you Junshine for bringing some shine into my dreary day
Also pretty good. Bad feet, but beer is good.

Worth doing for name alone. An yes these there climbs must be climbed together otherwise you get no points;  It's all there, black and white, clear as crystal! You stole fizzy lifting drinks! You bumped into the ceiling which now has to be washed and sterilized, so you get nothing! You lose! Good day, sir!
Yeah definitely shouldn't be climbing. Body is desecrated.
Good. Active Recovery.

Oh, what I'm gonna do to you. I'm so angry! First, I'm gonna tear your lips out. Yeah, that's what I'm gonna do. And then I'm gonna gouge your eyes out. Yeah, that's what I'm gonna do. Yeah, you're scared, huh? Next, I'm gonna tear your arms out of the sockets. And you wanna know what else? I'm gonna hit ya, and you're gonna fall, and I'm gonna look down, and I'm gonna laugh. But first, FIRST! I gotta take a whiz, don't you go anywhere, you stay right here, right on this spot, I'll be back.
ascents.zlaggableName: If That Augustus Gloop Looks At You One More Time...

ascents.comment: Ill kick his butt too.
ascents.zlaggableName: I'll Kick The Butt Of That Mike Teavee

ascents.comment: If this was more central, it would be done frequently. Nice. Booch. In my belly.
What does the guidebook have against people who suck at crack? You dot see me making fun of people who can't one arm. A one arm is V0 if you can do it. Good crack for those of us who suck at crack.
Actually quite good. Bottom moves are SUPER good. Top is a little scary but this is definitely a good climb. Active Recovery.
Worth doing. Active Recovery.
Active Recovery
I probably should not have climbed today.
Someone else did this!! Yay. Active recovery.
Wow, hard. Good fun. Friction is bad. No way Zen Flute will go.

I found shoulder buster beta that rocked my world. Good temps and whipping wind made every hold a jug. Andyliu84 your beta felt impossible, so I set up a drop knee and basically fell right hand into the start jug of To Kill Ya Corner. Tequilla time my boys!

Surprisingly hard start, but fun climbing overall! I enjoyed the beta I used for the top: big ol left cross to the pinch hold then drop right hand down to press and hand foot match. Decided to try this because there is no way this sausage man can do Zen Flute.

You know I'm such a fool for you
You got me wrapped around your finger
Do you have to let it linger?
Do you have to, do you have to, do you have to let it linger?
I Second GO-ed the OG in 2016 so this is a proud Third-GO! Waffleman going full pancake and sending the OG in the most inspiring way possible.

Tried this on that day where my max grade was V0 and never stuck the second move. But today I did the sit moves first try! Moral of the story, rest is good. Also gonna test Shirleys Hypothesis that drinking water makes you climb V10. Hopefully standing Kill in a few days!!
wow. incredible. I want to thank my crew for supporting me on my mega proj. So so good. cant wait to come back for Super Froz and Son of Safe Surfer - Footless. Going to be a good time.

MP gives this thing V7 but its quite a LORGE move with meh landing, so I thin the V8 is fair. If this was in Rocklands it would easily be V9. Speaking of Rocklands, this felt very Rocklands. Shoutout my breakfast food/human friend, the one and only Waffleman for finding this on MP. It is not in the book so even my 0-star-scowering eyes would never have found it. Also shout out the one and only Troy Fauteux for having this on the YouTube an his ever hilarious climbing antics.
I love the movement! And I love send beers. What a lovely unit we have up here, sending into the glorious cold of night. Get that Girthy Man some Pizza STAT!! He may die!

It was possibly too cold today. So cold that everything felt wet... either that or so cold our bodies felt incapacitated.  I knew this was in my future but i didn't know it would be today. Shoutout beer, today was Coronado Brewing and the Mountain Rambler. Classic combo, like peanut butter and gumballs. Always wanted to call this soft but after at least 69 goes i think this is probably solid V9. I wish there was a climb that was the first move repeated 10x, soft.

Rather fun. Part of a good tire your ass out circuit. The Orb was unobtainum today, but maybe next time a winter storm rolls in. Enjoyed the movement quite much. Felt like magicarp on the top out but I was rather tired you see. Chase managing to EEK his days climbed metric on david.vaskos.com with this sweet as climb.

Thank you Shriley for the camaraderie! If you weren't here i would  have drunkened all 6 beers and too loot for goodness sake. Kill on sight will go next time, dont you worry your pretty little brown eyes. That being said, shout out Rhino Skin TIP JUICE for apparently working. I climbed something notoriously sharp! Skin doing a good job when normally it just pisses the bed. Oh also shout out whoever Dyno-ed this, i wanted to and tried, but got scurred.

Wow. Weird day of odd conditions and weak bodies so figure id get a workout at the Sabres of Paradise area (that particular climb is fucked up... cant wait to epic). This climb is essentially one hard ass mofo move to a crimp, although I noticed a lot of heel hook betas online. Maybe that makes it feel more like 7. Liked more than I expected an it twas a good thrashing on the skin. Bring it on winter storm. Force me to rest.... i dare ya!
Movement was deeec, but dab rock behind you and top out were meh. Fitting this.
ascents.zlaggableName: supernova at the end of the universe

ascents.comment: I must have started lower than the "4A" loggers. Scott I hope you are well.

Dear Chas Walters,

I read these comments. I read them quite a lot. Yes I am a huge pussy, but today this pussy became a man. I am inspired by you good sir, and I hope one day I too can see a crack whore giving head by the clapper and two dogs fucking. 

I hope you are doing well, and know that you are in my thoughts today. 

P.S. this climb is fucking hard and miserable and i climbed it very bad. Only 3-4 sessions. Soft.

I liked this more than the OG, but still has some matchey pocket shenanigans that are just no fun. So deep in a valley right now, hopefully its a small valley and ill be recovered by tomorrow. But hey we got beer, and we got cheer.

If this tops out i did not do it, but the book makes it seem like it drops off. I literally could not have topped out if I tried, but i also had a flood light on the final jugs blasting me in the eye holes so it was a good time for everyone. Long walk back to the cars today.
Oh Scott!

Unnamed things are just the worst. Every FA'er has a moral imperative to name their climbs. It can be something super dumb, but unnamed climbs are like humans without souls. Help prevent soulless humans. Since no one does this I feel no shame in dubbing it Nowhere Ninja. Its the V4 to the left of highbrow. Its not great but hopefully its a little happy today.

What a hilarious flash attempt, and second attempt for that matter. First go had a classic fingers stuck in the pocket and fall on yout ass problem. Boy am i tired from one attempt at Sabers of Paradise. Nice Send train Isabel Waffle and me. Thanks shirley for getting food.

I'm glad the Legend Troy Fauteux thought this was hard too, although V7 might be stretching it. Going left is piss and straight up is just insane. But honestly?  even though i broke two feet, fell a good dozen times, lost a ton of skin, yarred on both a sharp two finger pocket and a mono, this may have been my favorite climb of the day. Those 0 start climbs sometimes surprise you. Also im a level 40 Pokemon GO player so you know i had to catch em all.
Scott you are sorely missed, and you are missing out. Ill drink an extra frosty morning day beer in your memory.

Surprisingly good! I think I may be on a traverse high! Some super cool pinch holds! It does feel short to be on the same level as the other insane happy traverses. Did not bring enough beer today unfortunately, but there is always tomorrow. I also tried sabres of paradise today... no dice. how is that thing v7. should have a route grade.
I thought this was going to be easy, but turned out to be tough. My fingers already hurt and I cant wait to go to Landscaping Duty. This is hand made quality shit were talking here.
ascents.zlaggableName: Work is a four letter word

ascents.comment: Did the OG 10 years ago, and this boulder passes the test of time. It is still as enjoyable as ever. That hole is so nice.

I got through the crux on the flash attempt but hadn't scoped the top because topping out is my style, and figured id be fine. It was a mistake. After chalking the top holds this went easy peasy I used big boy betas and spanned from underlining to good cramp. So many points on this boulder!! Points Points POINTS! Also apparently 4/5 is better than 3/3, thanks Kody for teaching me that!
I will always remember this thing as the Daniel Fong nipple ripper.

Wow! The V4 to V5 upgrade may not have been enough. This thing is nails. Marina almost pulled the incredible freak send with her jack the ripper fingers, but too much blood is just too much blood. On my send i tried too hard and jammed my fingers into the wall sticking the jug and cracked my nail quite good. This climb is beautiful and cimbs well but really is as stiff as rigor morits.

I'm good at math so let me handle this on. We will start with a V6, then we will add 5 moves which are harder than any sequence on the original V6., but we will still call it V6. The math works out. This thing is certainty harder than Skye Dance by a good margin. I needed it to help my booty warm up.

Thought it would go easy, than had to settle for the holy shit my left hand tips are getting gored I hope I can send. Fell once gracefully in the snow, but did eventually pull! Chase was inspiring on Dentons Remorse, and started the beer train! Choo Choo! Again I didnt bring enough beer...
Hard but good. Reach helps for the first move but really quite good moves on some sweet as crimps.
MSFGAWU. I was so cold I could not feel my body, my fingers, or my soul. Sweaty post hike bodies exposed to high winds are not conducive to good warming up. Not good at all. Fantastic climb.
I had never climbed on the thunder wall before today. Its amazeballs. This climb is hard as balls. The temperature was cold as balls. But it was also good as balls. Balls are very versatile.

Same hard first move as "Easy Cool", then a mongoid lock off that may be impossible if you are short. Its a little humid and my fingers were wet today so the hold you lock off to felt terrible. I couldn't bump to the jug, so had to lightening my right hand up for a quick snag. The lock off and pop are quite nice!
That was not nice and easy. Hardest V3 I have ever done, easily V5, could be V6. So yeah double upgrade here. 4 more boulders to my 8A2K!

Was in this little cave to to Pinball, but I left my chalk bag above the pinball hole so I climber this V3 to get it. The starting holds and first hold are cool and big, but the book didn't exaggerate, that reach is HUGE! and top is all dirty and stuff so probably clean it if you are gonna do it, but its not that great so probably dont worry. I couldn't believe how tired i was!! I couldn't finish pinball!

Pretty darn cool actually. Personally I like Jojos better, this basically turns into a traverse, whereas Jojos feels like the direct line. Jojos is a a little hard for V4 but this still feels like V6 even after the, break reported February 2021. Not sure what broke. Awesome holds on a roof! What a Bizarre Adventure!
A couple of campuses and a large reach later and you've done it!! One more to 8A2K!!!
Pretty darn cool feature wise. My toe hooks didn't stick so I held a wild one on the big hueco. Landing can be made pretty safe with pads! No bird poop on any holds today! What a pleasant surprise.

I've done it!! This is my 8A2K baby!!! 2,000 climbs logged on 8a. I wanna thank all my followers, my loving parents, sibling and friends, Petzle, Pokemon Go, Pure Project, and Tecnu. I couldn't have done it with out you all. Oh also Happy Birthday Chase!! And ill drink to that!

This is the dangit hole of all dangit holes! You could fit and entire tiny house down here. Its a little scary because it kinda looks like with some more erosion all the surrounding boulders could shift / fall! Rather enjoyable but nothing to write home about. I did use feet first beta to get to the first jug on the right arete, so that was cool! Top is choss.

Failed of 4 / 4 on my projects as well as Final Round... yet again.  But I did manage to do the highest possible start of the "Van Gogh" project. It starts two moves in,  but since its my first time topping the boulder and I live for days climbed metric I'm taking it.
The better of the two (Flake and Crack). Ingenious names here. Will climb again when out there. Tall enough for a little spice

There may be more to explore at Woodson. There is so much rock out here there is no way someone has looked at every side of every rock, right!? Cant wait to get more poison oak!

Fun tallish flake system, pretty thin that its honestly scary pulling out not down. May warm up on this pair in the future.

Failed on 4 / 4 of my projects but, I did this thing. Its to the right of "Final Round" about 15 feet, and starts about 10 ft off the ground above the classic oak tree. I really wanted a way to climb into the "start" holds, but it would be miserable and REALLY hard. If you shimmy between the rock and the oak tree you can reach the starting holds, paste a foot and pull on. A couple sweet crimps lead into "Ride the wave". Start on the good left-ish facing edge and a worse but opposing hold.

Flash FA! The classic combo! Located on the north corner of the Smurf /Gargamel boulder. Cool arete feature into a mantle encounter over a less than ideal landing.  Scare factor certainty adds to the mantle difficulty but this rig packs some good movement. Start on the obvious blocky jug thing work left and up to a big bump to a good hold, then a jug, then get your mantle hat on! Azrael is Gargamels cat. Nice kitty!

Thanks Kody for establishing this amazing gem! A little spicy, but once you know how to utilize the back rock its quite safe. Perfect rock with cool holds up and incredible face. Was quite bewildered that I bagged. Feels hard because the crux is rather low probability and rather high up. One of the best V8s on the mountain which says a lot because black is known for those. Much more attractive then the crusty wizard of whom it is named.

Its actually called "Unnamed Mantle" but as you all now I don't dig that. The yellow mantle on the rock behind "Gimme Some". That Traeblood got me thinking about pancakes. Who needs pads when a napkin will do. Rather impressed I flashed because everything felt insecure, but i had to impress Kody! As mantles go, its good.

Wow whee! Look's like it should be rather easy, but requires a ton of technique! Truly technical problems like this are rare, and it was very enjoyable working it out. I actually tried this back when I first saw "Dont tell anyone" but could't bag, and Kody finished her up a few weeks ago; good job adding another great line! Still sweet as FA's to be had at black!

Fun one mover! Some days I couldn't even pull off the ground, but the post rain cold friction and productive day at work just lifted me right up. Start left hand on the surprisingly hard-to-rip-off "tongue", and right hand on an opposing crimp off to the right. The feet are pretty bad.  If you train pinching wood 4x4 s this probably feels cakey. Make a big ol' move up to the jug and top out!

Might be V8, especially if the crux foot continues to crumble. It only broke on me like 7 times. One time I was high in the mantle placing my right foot next to my right hand when I got crimson chinned. It was a good one! That being said once I micro-ed the holds it felt rather repeatable.  Start in the scoop to the left of Moon as my Wittness, get a high left foot, grab a micro sharp crystally bastard and mantle that shit. Once mantelled you still have a tenuous step up! Fun! Project 10 on MP.

Finally put it together. Didn't feel too bad today, but another one that some days I cant even pull off the ground. Start right hand on the obvious ear crimp, that may rip off one day. Left hand anywhere on the opposing sloper feature. Surprisingly hard slaps get you up. I am curios if a lower start goes to both this and "polyglot"! Food for drewbie when he comes.
Quite fun. That crimp is just awesome. Obviously contrived, but worthwhile nonetheless. Shade is nice sun is hot. Still cant do Juniors Achievement. I'm seriously upgrading that when I do it.
#14. A good arete with flakes to warm up!
I've never been on Boys and Girls before!
One crazy climb into another! Sharing beers with friends is best! Stoked Kevin was super into the Belching PB stout. Cheers my dude.
Awesome to meet up with Lisa out here in Bishop! Pleasure meeting Sav, Christie and Kevin as well. Fun day at the milks. I am no longer used to day climbing, temps feel way worse.

I thought this would be miserable pulling through several two finger pockets to link the infamous Alex Patterson into The Orb Short, but flowed way better than I expected. I cant wait to FA and area called Alex Patterson and name every single climb Alex Patterson. Its gonna be good.

What an incredible day ladies and gentlemen! So long, and that second crux is total limit. Used clutch and much to early no hands kneebar rest in the hueco; excited to use that new "With Kneepad" 8a.nu tag! Another great day climbing with Nacho and Lisa! Also Orange Crush!

Quite nice! Hard to imagine this being V9 when its basically a shortcut of Sabres of Paradise. Heel hook beta for Sabersonic crux is much better in both enjoyment and ease. I have now done everything on this boulder! I guess I could do Super Jack of Swords if I ever end up back here. Big shoutout the one and only human waffle for surpassing he limits and going beyond plus ultra to bag Alex Patterson!

Holy cow my Goose Egg day was saved by a flying man in a loincloth! By that I mean Lisa told me this was a climb and I did it. Rad feature. Would world class if the feature continued for more than like 1 move. Lisa with an inspiring day sending Rios quickly in some beautiful and softly falling wet snow then soft second going Water Hazard right.

That's two votes in favor!! Felt destroyed but Chooch with the inspiring Hamtaro send gave me the chutzpah I needed to pull this. Send train baby! Technically speaking there was a "dab" or two during the no hands rest =P, but well, they were good dabs. That no hands rest kind of makes the first 20 feet of the traverse pointless.... I guessI'm a sport climber now!
Also need to should out Dan and Josh for making their first Bishop trip! Proud of you guys are sticking with climbing!
Very fun and equally easy! Nice Combo!

second GOOOOOO. Would have flashed but they crew got in my head about it being impossible to flash and that Kody didn't really flash he is just deluded. Waffleman giving me amazing  beta which I absolutely did not use. Chases beta was Vnice. Body pretty wrecked, almost bagged Swanky Sit but there's always next time!

Nothing quite like climbing all week and wait until the morning of the last day of your trip to try your proj lol. I'm bad at resting so my body was devastated.  Thanks Chooch for both the psyche and the tp, both were vital to my sending. Honestly very cool moves, the ice caves are just an awesome formation. Its amazing how bad the crux right foot feels until one burn and then it just never blows again. Thanks for an unforgettable week, Chooch!

First face you see when walking into the Hanging Gardens and despite is obvious beauty it went undone for so long! Vertical face with just enough holds to be possible. Such interesting delicate movement which requires so pretty serious micro . Might be easier that V9 but it is hard to grade a puzzle.  So proud! Definitely one of my better FAs and definitely my best addition to Woodson so far. There is potential for a Sit as well! Nothin like a Pure Project Quad to celebrate, Kody you missed out!

I hope this has been done before me, but its not on MP even though it is such a glorious line! Slot yourself in between bowser and Waluigi and ride the most obvious crack feature up and left for a good 20 feet of climbing before a perfect mantel. Watch out for oncoming traffic! Slightly contrived but hey, we are boulders for a reason! My Mario Kart references no longer make sense because I corrected the name to "The Patio" to be consistent with older guide books of woodson!

Wow. Crimpers and hang board masters all, come see this new one move wonder! Start with left on a good slightly right facing crimp in the low seam below "The Patio" and right hand another hold in the seam. Pull on and do a surprisingly hard campus into the jug side pull ~8 feet into "The Patio". Then finish her up. Reminiscent of the classic shortcut on the N64 track. Could definitely start one set of holds further left but it felt fucked. Would be cool though!
SO good. I've walked by this thing probably 2 dozen times and always wondered if it went. WAY easier than expected, but at the same time EXACTLY as good as I expected. Will for sure repeat often.
Not as good as the left but still good

I spent a few hours trying the "I love big dicks" AKA "ImATinyMan" AKA  "The Hulk want some Love" AKA "Squeeze Me Sweetly" Project. It literally fucked me. At this point its 9pm so I decided to do the classic roadside stuff I've never done before. This climb is actually quite good and lives up to the hype. Great holds, and fun varied movement.
Meh. On the other hand, very enjoyable call with Chooch on the hike down

Another one I've looked at tons and always thought would be harder! Really fun, top might be able to be done smoother but meh didn't expect to get there first try. Suddenly Hamburger Crack Area may be one of my new go to places... although I hate crowds... also I am on a quad high right now. Thank Pure Project!

Was tossing a lot of potential names around for this one but the water has finally settled, just keep swimming. Thanks Dory! Crazy friction dependent. Basically compressing up a full extension rounded feature on frustrating feet. Amazing weekend with Lisa! Only stayed out here till just after midnight. I love that we sat at the blasted boulder to do Duolingo together; don't lose those streaks! Also Lisa you throw  a mean left elbow hook!
ascents.zlaggableName: And He Shall Be My Squishy

ascents.comment: This is named in honor of a fabulous weekend with Lisa. How many people stay out bouldering past midnight? Of those how many take a Duolingo break at 11:50 to not lose their streaks!? Lol! So awesome to share this quirk with Lisa. We successfully saved our streaks both at Woodson yesterday and today at RPC. It t'was an unforgettable record setting weekend indeed. Should have let Lisa try this first since she cruised it! I've been trying it for a few sessions and it makes a great addition to RPC
5pm - Midnight almost escapes the heat. Almost.

Wow. What a day. I sometimes suck at climbing. Fourth session on Monkey Bar direct and no dice. Got slapped around by My Tan and the Bathtub as well. Ouch. Days climbed metric Baby! Nice send of MB Right Lisa!

That's another for hat fall off bingo! Woot! Holy poly this thing became a Homer lengthed epic for me. So hard. Why can I flail on it the day before, then come back more tired, hotter temps, wetter tips and having forgot to morning poop and send M Soft First Go? Classic climbing. Oh, that's right I brought a better send beer this time! Thanks Lisa and Kim for a great trip and amazing support on this saga.
AKA Lisa and Kim dance party. Same thing start but slink under the Moran dab and go left.

Actually kind of fun. Paying around staying warm while Lisa and Kim work Moran! Dodging the Moran boulder to top out is both super annoying and makes the climb. Had to actually put my climbing shoes on. I rocked off on a preliminary burn and crushed a beer can rather adeptly with my ass.

Thought it might be fun and hard to go from the gleaner start holds right to the jug you toe hook and finish up Joseph. Way easier than I expected but not too shabby! Way to go Lisa slaying Acid Wash Right on a perfectly executed burn!

Days climbed metric secured.  Decent climb and fair warm up. Cruisers + padless is classic. Good 420 smells at the crag. I also learned Woofer is spelled WFR, those practice screams were legit. Also this climb is my middle name.
I thought this was wonderful, Thanks Rembrandt! Hall of Mirrors, beyond being a popular pooping spot has a few nice moderates.

Never had a desire to do this one but It's actually rad. Fun holds the hole way and a nice gentle slab angle. Would be a fantastically popular warm up if it was more central. Lisa having another great day today putting down Orange Crush and French Connection! Good ol' orange crush!
Crushing the hall of mirrors one low grade softie at a time! Great Job Isabel getting two MSFGs on 'WORK is a four letter word' and Acid Wash Right! That deserves a beer!

Amazing V3, cant believe I never hear this one being recommended. Maybe we just suck at saying French things here so we don't even try. Pretty face, nice holds, fun crux and good landing. May be a tad hard for V3, but get on it!
There's a big move on this one! who would have guessed! Overall the boulder is small and modest.
This thing has the potential to climb more awkward than a Giraffe giving birth...

Is it possible to have a climb that is so gross, that its actually awesome? I thought that would be impossible but this climb has done it! So much fun throwing myself at this thing with Chase and groping knobs while drinking beer. Seriously hard this one. Classic funky pinch flip to meat hook.

I was going to log this as N.N or Unknown, but there is a true artist among rock creek boulders. I love the name and will tell all my friends. I was so wet a greasy by the end it was a real nice time.

Wow redemption after missing my chance to send before last season ended. My skin is just the worst so I was honestly worried it might not go today. Second or so burn of the day I held it together and took it to the top, topping out WAY better than Shirley. Seriously that guy looked real bad up there.  Only crumbled the first overzealous gaston a few times with my foot: luckily its big enough to still be good after loosing like a millimeter or two. A tad soft, but clearly harder than overzealous.

Miracles happen every day boys and girls. So do shitty things. Remember that. Saw someone just dyno this climb from pretty low on the inter webs and decided to try the same. Surprised myself with a clean snag on the ~second burn of the day. Great temps, great friend and great beer always help. Close on the sit but it eats your fingers. I got to the dyno once from the ground, but was in utter disbelief that I stuck the dyno from such shitty feet. Next time! PSF for Lisa on The Fluke!

A aesthetic face truth be told, but tis a silly place... lets not go to Camelot. Stack a few pads then pull one decent fingery face move to easier top. But yes certainly should not be in the same league as Osama...
Very soft... honestly the V4 feels the same difficulty. But what would I know I'm not a doctor.  Cool variation through, rosed under for the match out right.

Felt awful at morning yoga, then was pleasantly surprised by a closed Looney Bean kitchen forcing us to get delicious food across the street at an amazing Cuban food truck! Ate too much deliciousness, and spice and had to walk it off by showing Lisa Checkerboard. After a pre send poop, and a pre send fail, I finally managed to bag. Way easier than Fall Guy, harder than Fly Boy, maybe low end but felt V9. Took a full value swing latching the top!

Pretty sure I tried this a long time ago with Jess Chen and may have made an absolute fool of myself in more ways than one. My sincerest apologies.  I had the craziest Deja Vu on the top out, and had to search my logs to verify if id actually done this or now. I vaguely remember climbing this in a dream... what a shitty climb to dream about. But it was fun today.
Some fun moves, definitely needed the friction. Meh, something new to do.

Miracle send honestly. Easy bonus V points once you have the top dialed. Those razor blades are miserable but they don't add to much difficulty. Why could I not put this together the other night when I still had skin and fuel in the tank? A quad, a hazy, a booch and a smoothie style ale was apparently all the inspiration I needed. Shoutout Waffleman for cruising Overzealous and punching The Fluke and winning the bleed on the pads bet. Had a genuine presend flail and Chooch got the whole thing!
(direct) - Just as hard as the OG but a cool tenuous variation.

Thought this would be my best chance at a V9 flash, so much Gregor style it has! Might have been feasible if it wasn't my 5th day on,  but when in Rome, climb like you will never climb again. Harder than it looks, especially working though the right hand slopers. Found slightly different betas than what the interwebbers use, and felt nice to me. Awesome climb. Thanks Shirley for locating, Chooch for support+vid and Nach for being a trooper through the over hiking and bush wacking!

(PRNF - Pending Real Name Found). This is the sit start of the face on the back side of the Mad Hatter. Anyone who comes to this boulder has probably warmed up on this thing before doing the Mad Hatter. The stand is maybe a V2 but the sit adds a kinda cool, kinda really awkward but entertaining start. Start sitting on the south side of the boulder on a pretty obvious corner edge. Pull in to the cool side pull system, into some good edges and ultimately the arete to top.

Was hoping to pull another miracle and send Lawnmower man today but those moves are too powerful and I could feel the starts of tendonitis hell. 6th day on is too much. Lisa did cruise French Press with style and crucial swiftness for us to make her flight in time! Anyway, is this climb effing hard or is it just me? Climbs super well, but I had a large DP to the lip which was mildly scary. Days climbed metric baby!

My knees were very happy to have the 4 pads for this. Dyno from the left facing Crimp Jug (to the left of the "river") straight to the top. You can sit start way down on the underclings if you want and off route the entire river, but the beginning is such choss you might just pull a 75 pound piece of rock on top of yourself. Once that choss falls off, it may be a cool sit. Wanted to give this V8 but damn I still cant to "Final Round" so it cant be.

Tested out the new 2x Big Organic, 2x Small Organics and 1x Send Blubber today. The watermelon family was happy to have an outing together. On trails without anything above me my new set up is casual. The last steep bush cave part into hanging gardens was tough. That being said stoked to keep improving my fitness! This climb starts on the same jugs as The River Tirgis but doesn't use any holds to the right of the "river". May be reachy, but cool last move.

Adam Burch Memorial Slab Problem. Many SEASONED slab masters have done this and I've seen someone do this, but I still think there is a chance that its an FA. I do have big BALLz. Anyway, this thing is contrived and terrifying, but you get to use two HONKER knobs. I bet you like that Adam. There is a 10`+ fall to your right w/ bad landing as you smear on shit to stab out to the foot knob. To the right of Cheap Thrills, go right, up is not allowed. Also 4 full pts go staight to the final honker.

This is a tall boulder with a bad landing. Fitness such as mine is mucho importanto if doing this alone 4x pads is a minimum. There was/is alot of shit rock low, but cleaning up nice-ish. Also, trying to not dab on the "crack" side pulls is tough. That left chunk is def not on, good thing a boulderer FA'ed this. Start on rad left facing holds in a dang-it location and movement is only saved by a glorious to hook out right. AMAZING rock over to top out ~25 feet on SEASONED slab.
Climb all the things. Get back into climbing shape body, damnit!

Got 2nd Maderna Saturday morning, did yoga, helped demo and reinstall some Latice work for my boy Shawn during which I started to get the vaccine fever... had a beer after finishing then went home with the intention of packing for my flight Sunday but i literally couldn't move... the rumors are vitamin I is bad for vaccine strength so I  proceeded to sweat and shiver all night watching God knows how much Avatar: The Last Airbender in an attempt to sleep, which i couldn't. (continued in Cue Ball)
Really proud of myself for being able to climb 3a. Maybe im ready for Beyond Life.
OG book gives V4 but its next to Footmare which is like 4 grades harder. Not bad climbing tho
Fuck this thing is hard.

I finally woke up.... well I never really fell asleep so more like slithered out of bed around 10am and tried packing. My head hurt so bad i could only pack like 1 item every 10 minutes. My flight was at 2pm and somehow the ridiculously slow 6 items per hour was fast enough to get some semblance of packing done and my sister drove me to the Airport. I'm finally starting to feel like a living organism again and i successfully navigate to my gate.  As soon as im seated i fall asleep (thank god)...

Little hollow, but honest. 5 Years and it would have been longer except for Chooch planning this rad work from home in  Orangeville and climb at night Woot Woot! We finished unpacking at our AirBnB at like 8pm so classically we started climbing then and went till about 1am, adding chexmix to the list.
Just shove those big meaty sausages up into the slotty crimpy underclings and pull on why dont ya?
Over 5 years since I've been here
It may be v0 but dont let the grade fool you. I had to actually put my shoes on to send. Suddenly got the goal to send everything in Boysize tonight! Can he do it!?

No, no he cant. When you start climbing after 8pm there simply isnt enough TIME. Unless of course you are playing the 9hour Hans Zimmer version. Would be a pretty cool circuit to just do everythign at boysize for fittness, i mean seriously who needs a gym, right Shirley?

...and literally slept the whole flight! I never sleep on planes and i fell asleep BEFORE take off and woke up during landing. Got to my connecting flight in SLC to St George where Lisa picked me up! She almost convinced me to climb at Moe's right then but sleep was more important. Woke up Monday worked some, then continued to work through the 3 hour drive to Orangeville! Definitely in prime climbing condition my dudes adn dames! Lets GO!
Another climb i think
Also did I mention I barely climbed the last 2.5 weeks since my middle fingy on my right hand has been sore. I'm also new era 165lbs so yeah, nothings good on TV, conditions are perfect.
Another goodie! That start hold is nutty! It looks like a sloper... but its a pocket jug! Felt hard for me but what would i know I'm just a weak weak boy, That crux right hand is vbad, .

more of a big ol DB. That would have been a hilarious name "More of a big ol DP" lol. Good fun. Lisa and I rock the weather gods. It may be late may but temps cometh. Especially if you climb at night its plush. May make WFH in joes in May a regular thing.

Not much to warm up on here. Shoutout the amazing trail maintenance and landing maintenance by the climbing community and or the city of Orangeville. things are crisp and safe these days. This climb has some nice moves and be sure to clean the top first for that technical mantle!

I love the sand paper grip on these sweet as holds. Would love to come back for the sit some day but definitely need more time than just a week out here. Sandbox brainwashed me into thinking that Joes sucks, but there is so much good shit! I want to spend like a month out here. So much good stuff i haven't even seen!
Honestly, this would have been a world class V0 if the jugs just continued a few more feet. Dishonestly, its a good V4. Clean the top dudes and dames,
Perfect climbing. And unlike Dirk i was not fooled by the sidepull out right and pulled the flash,.

Harder than I expected, and quite a bit better than I expected. Name honestly makes it sound terrible, but its not. Also believe it or not, third day climbing in joes and we have not climbed with even a single other climber. what!? How is that possible. Maybe its the fact its late may, maybe its the fact that its mid week, or maybe its the facct we climb super late. Anyway, this makes joes infinitely mroe enjoybale. Having the place to yourself is bliss.

I don't know if I am recovered from my vaccine yet honestly... all the late nights certainty doesnt help. Anyway, all those excuses were weighing me down quite a bit making that crux throw even mroe massive. Much better climbing that i expected for a wee lowball.

So much aesthetics just wow. Way hard this boy. Me not the boulder, heehee. JK i meant the boulder. I had to just jump for the jugs from the slopey lip which lead to a vnice hero swing. The jugs are covered in this weird calciferous ooze that make my hands smell like the Wild Animal Park, AKA animals, poop dust and leaves. Lisa though it smelle a bit like pot: I guess i have pot hands now.
Should have flashed but i forgot to concur,
Thanks Laura for the Rec. Quite nice. Getting ready for AMF Mar Vista, with my boys. If only I had some bowling shoes too Id be ready to go!
What do you know! Here's some shoes! Lets Bowl Boys, then do a classic trifecta afterwards? Im down.

mflash. Maybe I finally caught up on some sleep, or the lingering effects of my second dose finally wore off, because I'm literally Paul Bunyan. Watch me swing my Axe my dudes and dames, and stick that sweet-as campus crux.
Bleu the flash being a swan. Put on my duck hat instead and it went nicely. Not actually a lip traverse despite what it looks like. This may surprise you but remember, "Why is the duck, the duck?"

Blooo the mflash being corporeal. I should have worn my ghost shoes. This climb is simply amazing. In the words of Faniel Dong, this thing is D O Penis. I almost forgot that fun phrase from our college days. Howling winds and post sunset temps made my fingers stickier than a klepto. Wanted so bad for this to feel hard so I could upgrade. Too bad. As you might expect being a king of mantelling I made the top look smooth as a babys bottom.

blue the flash being  a wanker. Thanks Isabel for the great recommendation, much fun this one. Finally climbed with other climbers today! Wow, I've been getting spoiled having all of Joe;s to ourselves. Shout out Zach with an "h", stoked to have timed things perfectly to spot you on your flash of Tubesnake Boogie. Keep on dancing my dude, maybe climb with you today.

Those features make me desperately want to make love to a school boy! errr... well I mean... ahem, lets try again. Those features are so cool that I feel giddy like a child again, so much magic and infinite possibilities, that I am almost falling in love. Nailed it. What was all that one in a million talk? So stupider & stupider-ly soft.
Climbed well yesterday so figured I would today too... those damn stone boobies took more out of me than i expected... time for impromptu rest day!

Fourth go, another one I should have flashed but I am a tired boy. I've looked at this thing many times and thought it looked gross, I mean that first crimp to get to the arete looks so broken it probably needs surgery. That being said, the feet are so good, its enough to get you to the immaculate and picturesque arete.

I wish I was fresh bc this could have been my first V9 (soft) flash. I like the MP description as a "3D" boulder! It really is and it climbs super fun! A little morpho for sure (at least for the easiest beta), but it looks like there are options for all sorts of folks, human or otherwise. My crux was holding the swing when ripping the heel. It was a little balsy to bring the Champagne here having never sent a V9 in joes, but I figured I could pull! Woot woot! Cheers my dudes and dames!
Its.... snowing!? What? Honestly?  Thank you, Lenny. Wow! You know, a lot of people said winning this award four years in a row couldn't happen. Well, I guess I showed...

Not in the original guide? huh. I guess it is kinda far away from the Fingerhut block. 50 feet is just too much! Maybe it used to all be choss, or maybe there was shit in the landing.. who knows. Unirregardlessly this is a fun climb. I did a huge jump for the meathook top which was nice.

I was so excited to climb today that it was hard to sleep last night! That rest day got me feeling like its bouldering Christmas Eve! Joes seriously has so much I want to climb, must come back soooooon.
Three men in a tub! well almost... I wish anyway. A fun little compression prow.
First go. Listed on MP as "Shark Bait", this is the right version of Great White. Just as good, maybe better depending on your style and climbing preference even!

stg. This "recommend" is conditional. I did the low start and the first two moves are SO dumb that they literally should burn in hell. Why in gods green earth would you force an annoying match to get into the OBVIOUS start jug? From the jug this climb is all time, from the left crimps, still all time but annoying. I vote the move the start hold to the obvious jug. From the lower crimps is solid 8, from the jug its soft 8 so who really cares! Take the points and swing away dear boys and girls!
At least this was a third go and not a second (tried the dyno after failed flash attempt). So good! Such nice holds. If topping this out was a race, I would have won gold. Speed manteller here.

This second go curse is getting real annoying. Does anyone have magical powers and can fix me? How did I forget there was a massive jug to my left? Damn witch in the forest and that questionable voodoo. I still aaaalllmost stuck it skipping the left jug, but "almost" is not the same as "is". Rad climb, V7 does seem fair.

I did it my dudes and dames! I haven't eaten since last November and it was just want I needed to flash this rig! Def did not climb well, but I had my main man Stev squirt me down with perfect top out beta on the fly. Proceeded to wreck myself on Meat Eater. This roof is rad.
This climb makes me really think of Ryan, and how many dead babies he could fit. Probably not a whole number.

Climbed like 4 moves in using the back wall and Lisa was like, "oh yeah the apron is off", to which I was like "I'm not cooking right now of course my Apron is off", so I reversed back to the starting block and did it apron less without touching the ground to preserve the flash. This with Baby Coffin make some of the Best V3s I've done in a while.

Aka "Fucktard" and "Tater Toes". Interesting single mover this boy. I did not try the shoeless beta, but sounds titillating.  The move isn't very far, but its is surprisingly precise and it seems like your knee and body are in the way.
Not 100% sure on the name. It the boulder to the left of The Brain and the full traverse from left to right. Another boulder with a lot of fun warm up variations.
AKA "Island Living". Did it as a big ol' jump since first holds are jugs and so is the top. Enjoyable. Warming up, honestly sacred the draw might destroy me, don't climb roofs like at all!

Oh so lovely. Also called "Ant Farm" some places, but this is certainly in contention for one of the best easy blocks ever. Like a way better Dragon Scales form JTree. Unlimited Variations, good for gentle warm up. I would love to see how many people could possibly fit on this wall at the same time. I'm thinking like two full sandboxes.

Pretty hard last move for V2 not gonna lie. Good fun. I didn't realize that Flagstaff was like high elevation. Its liek really nice out here, you see those trees? You see that water? Yeah life is pretty good. I really like the ambience and ecosystem of the Draw.

I guess traditional beta is to use the cool pinch the WRONG way and go feet first. Not sure if that is easier or harder but going to the pocket, crossing to pinch then holding the massive swing on the adjacent jug was rad movement wise. Another one I should have flashed but tried dumb beta, then dabbed, then finally og third go.

AKA "Big Slaps" Hand full of goes. Started to think it wouldn't go bc that sloper is p bad, and so is the top sloper, but then I realized I've never even been to Mount Vesuvious and the top sloper was just subtle. Olaf was very proud. Nice to finally meet the legend PANG!

Like seriously, these roofs are nutty and more featured than a PPnJ with extra crunchy peanut butter. Henry tried to scare us into breaking our leg on this, but I'm happy to say I didn't. It is quite left heel intensive through.
A wee tricky but cool. MP calls it "Pinch a Loaf" but that is like just copying the climb two over. This name is nicer.

PRNF: (Pending Real Name Found) - on the left of Monster Roof there is a very hard "V4" which is literally the hardest thing on the wall besides "Barb and Star Groovy". It has a big move to a pocket then you find another pocket. I heard Stanko couldn't do this one when he tried to clear the roof Muahahah! I cleared the roof, time for a beer!

Best on the wall. Another 3rd go that should have been a flash,  getting in that sick toe hook was tricky and I couldn't find it on the flash.  I tried to just squeeze like a sasquatch but it wasn't enough. Lisa told me to open my hips like butterfly pose to get the toe hook in and after sussing the toe penetration once it went down like The Hazy IPA I am currently libating
A good warm up toward the left of Monster Roof
Am I beautiful yet? Researching good treatments for scars to make sure the one on my face doesn't keloid. Honey, Garlic or vitamin E apparently. Call me Honey face from now on, Gregor is sweet.

Last move is the realness. Loaf feature is sick, and blind throw from said loaf is also sick bc you don't need eyes. Applied my puzzle solving brain to find as many ways to do that last move as possible so hopefully one of them is soft for Chooch! Campus variation is DOP
Very cool, very soft. Those aren't heel hooks, they are heels cemented in buckets.
Roofs for days my dudes and dames. Another good one here. Didn't think I would go feet first at the end, but when i got there, I did.

I have done many easier dynos with significantly larger V numbers. That being said, first time pulling on is a little scary! You start on that raised shelf and it takes at least one tentative go to feel comfortable with the fall. I am able to keep the right hand which make the swing significantly easier. Mucho Funo.

Nice! I literally haven't grabbed a flat crimp in all of priest draw!  That makes this problem kinda unique for the area. Cool DP from the start namesake crimp flake , then classic face climbing to better holds.
On Plaque wall, left of "Flexi Flake" make one crux move up and left to a good hidden pocket, or don't realize the pocket it there and do some good sloper pulls.
You shouldn't... because thats MY side boob! The more "obvious" line compared to "Man Tits" Start on good pockets and move through the gastoning dishes.

Def V5, That first move is quite large, and to another one of those elusive Priesty crimp edges. I also off routed all holds to the left which adds another hard sequence to slap some slopey holds to finally get the overhead jug.
So many warm ups today! I may be too tired to actually climb!
From the same start holds as the warm up, feels forced and kinda dumb.

I really like this boulder, and this position. Biggest downside is its too short, just like my duration. But at least its not as short as Ishmael Matinyman, poor guy. This boulder raises the tell take question: "Can I start with my heel in"?. I don't actually know the answer  so I started by campusing my heel in. May be the difference between "soft" and "not soft"
More climbing.

I will admit there was a noticeable dab when I was forced to hold a ridiculous swing when i used v-shitty beta. I'm sick of second go's and since I know that we are living in a simulation, I asked the simulation moderators if i would have held the swing. She (god maybe) said "let me check", after a few milliseconds she said "Yep, there wasn't even a single simulation in this or any parallel universe where you would not have held that swing". I said, "nice", and gave her a sweet high five.
Wow... that hueco is not that good.

One of the biggest problem with roof climbing is gross underclings... this has those. Still a great problem just be prepared to throw up in your mouth a little. First climb I have ever needed one shoe off to make it easier. I did the large boy beta with a bang-on cross to the good right hand in a JBS way then used my shoeless left big toe to pull on the deep incut pocket to fall left hand into that surprisingly bad undercling. From there top is cheese. Harder than Anorexic for me sooo probs V7.

Cruxy deadpan to a 2 finer pocket! YIKES! First move is humongoid, but somehow not too bad. Match is a little annoying with big ol sweaty sausages, but with a nice left heel toe cam it was chill piggy party shuffle. Much tape needed to make the two finger pocket bearable. This much climbing in priest draw is making my hands hurt in weird places! I'm used to just tips being raw, not the sides of every finger!
Classic getting asked what climb this is while you are climbing. I must have climbed this terrible bc it felt total limit.

I feel kind of bad but I could never remember the name of this and always just called it "That Jesus Christ Problem". When you are used to roofs where every hold is a jug, the holds on this surprise you by being shitty. Some fun thrutchy moves!

I think hiking is 3B... so I'm gonna upgrade to V0. By Triangle Arete I mean the amazing and tall left Arete of the Triangle Boulder. This recommend is for the WHOLE boulder, the brain is sick and all but this is one of the best warm up boulders ever and this Arete is just peach perfect. So many variations, great landing and aesthetic. Must do boulder in the area. I apologize for all the variations I am about to add... there goes my average grade metric!
Start on Triangle Arete (the left arete) the follow the prominent and juggy diagonal crack up and right that starts about half way up.
Start in basically the center of the face and just go straight up, forget if I sat start or stood start.

Start on a left facing hold about 6 feet right of the left arete, directly above the "detached" foot block. Without using the "detached" foot block move up and right through some gastons into the good pocket and up.

Start on a left facing hold about 6 feet right of the left arete without using the "detached" foot block. Instead of heading up and right move up and left through some surprisingly small gastons to join the juggy crack.
Start on the right-ish side of the face and go straight up.
V easy. But nice. Again this boulder is a heavy weight in the easy warm up class.

Starting "matched" in the low pocket feature is at least V5. Left hand was in a labyrinth of a pockety under cling and right was 2 inches lower in a shallow 2 finger pocket. Starting one more move in is a jug walk. Did not go feet first which was kind of cool bc led to a massive swing.

Def the area test piece. My crux was rotating my hand on the banana hold. Favorite move was putting my foot on the ballsack. Rest day does wonders, even if it was full of acrobatics and slacklining leaving you more sore that before. Majestic Marketplace delivered with some DOP beers making this send taste delicious. Amazing first trip to the draw, cannot wait to come back and start trying Mars Roof!

Did this after the low, and it climbs quite differently (except last 2-ish moves). This seems like one of the #KeepTheDrawStiff climbs, either that or #ImATiredTiredBoy because this felt every inch of V7. I climbed it sqrt differently than other videos on the internet but it was great fun. Again seriously the best finish hold in the Draw.

"Floor Pie Low" is quite confusing, I guess there is a "Low Right" and a "Low Left". The low left is more obvious and better documented on the interwebs, so that is the one I did. Start on jugs in the back left of the cave and do a MASSIVE move into the starting slot of the stand. Work some magic to get back to the arete. My beta was brilliant and I was never even close to dabbing, and actually climbed v-beautifully. Seriously felt like V9 but I'm a tired tired boy. Best finish hold in the Draw.
ascents.zlaggableName: Floor Pie Low aka The Lumberjack

ascents.comment: I haven't been since late January 2019! Woohoo!
WAY harder than I expected. You gotta get deep. Deeper than Peter Gibbons in his hypnosis! That's real deep boys and girls. So much viterbation material from this trip, Stoked!

Good warm up. I guess the "real" Boomerang continues left more, but this version was good as well, and a nice warm up. Its odd, its hard to "trust" rock you haven't really climbed on before. I guess I'm so used to bullet proof granite so i think all other rocks are just going to choss into pieces even if they wont.
Another less direct line that starts on the same holds as "Mikes Arete" but adds a few moves by busting out right with a cool move.
Kinda good. Start holds are picture perfect (Especially that left hand jug!), but game changer is way more alluring even though this is the most "direct" line.

Rad drop knee move! Very fun. So glad Lisa brought me out to the Supes! I thought I might not get to see any local Phoenix spots bc its summer and its hotter than Satan's asshole. We left for the Supes at 7pm, started hiking at 8pm and it was only mid 80s when we started climbing at 8:45! Sending temps choo-choo! Climbed until about 1am and got home at about 3am. What a night! Didn't snag game changer but was close, but more importantly we added it to the list.
Saguaros are so amazing! I love them. Like seriously they are such a fantastic creature. Tall and proud.  How do they grow? Outward like a tree? or do they extrude? This climb is also quite good.

Skin is screaming from Game Changer. Saw some tarantulas tonight which was cool. Would have loved to work "Public Enemy" but I am wrecked! Fire burning in the distance was both rad and eerie giving the area a Mordor like feel. I guess the fire is still burning as I write this which is bad new bears. Poor Saguaros!

Another good one! Fortress is pretty dense! Wanna come back and try way more here. Almost flashed but I am a tired tired boy and couldn't quite hold the bad beta one arm swing. Lisa told me a top hold was good and let me tell you, it was most certainty not. Almost blew it.

What is the secret of your power?
won't you take me far away from the mucky-muck man,

Right hand crimping was hurting my middle finger so I came up with this rad high left heel to cross left hand to the slopers and rode the heel till the sick incut then had a large jaump to the jug. This thing is quite good, the contrivance of the left rock is sad, but movement is so fun. This climb literally feels like two boulder problems stacked on each other. Each half is very different style but both rad.
That Carl is so hot right now. Took me many more burns than the right harder version. The move is big but not hard once you find beta.
Very cool. Big ol move to a big ol hold then a little bit of top out spice. Must do of area.

insanely hard for V4, especially in not so ideal conditions. That sloper is bad bad bad. Features are cool though. Didnt wnat to look bad in front of Christian, Laura, Sergio, Julia, Nikki and (I forgot last girls name im sorry!) is the only reason I sent!
AKA Hot Carl left. I liked it. Squeezy Squeezy juggy goodness.

Another awesome small AZ crag! So many different environments and rock types. A good feel here with lovely trees. Nice to climb with some of Lisa friends for a hot sec! No one likes to do the late nights like us lol. Well I guess this night we did meet up with Kim and Joe at Anorexic and then for food at Karma which was fantastic! Loved the classic double reverse Kim tried to pull =P. Glad you ended up coming to hang!
From the online vcrux guide. Warming up. Tops are very dirty
From the online vcrux guide. This one is the best of the warm-ups, goes up the cool stepped corner!
From the online vcrux guide. Warming up. Tops are very dirty
From the online vcrux guide. Warming up. Tops are very dirty

Best line on the boudler! Mantle is SO rad. A left flip, a right press, a left pop, a left foot up and one more left flip and away the news goes! Knew this would be a little scary and i was right bc you land basically in the bush which makes falls wonky. 

So tired today carrying 4.5 pads in the hot sun. 3am bedtime last night definitely didnt lend iteslf to climbing strong. But at least i got days climbed metric wtih this boy!

Quick Igor session before parents get here! So tired. I love the shade of Igor. Drew make a name for this climb otherwise it will remain Earfquake. Kind of dabby kind of annoying and a drop off, but good climbing!

I did this to commemorate the hike I did! Not longest but def hardest I have ever done. 6 peaks 5ish lakes 21 miles 9000 foot elevation gain. Up Eagle Lake > White Chief Peak > Vandaveer Mountain + false peak > Farewell Gap > Tulare Peak > Upper Franklin > Rainbow Mountain, sketchily down the backside thru gorgeous valleys with HUGE boulders > Amphitheater Lake > crystal pass > Mineral Peak > down Crystal trail. Eileen met me with Black Tuesday 1 mile out! Cheers!

Chossy little rock next to a big even chossier rock. Wouldn't be bad movement if you could trust the gory darn rock. Dont you wish this virility would last forever? My father made it to Timber Gap today but he has since said many dark comments about the lost years of youth. The down hill was miserable for him =[.  I went to Empire Mountain in the time it took him to descend......

Yes I got death by Mountain Lion on my mind. Walked through a copse of Junipers with two freshy dead birds and  a lot of shit before i happened on this boulder. Will be back for the awesome roof drop off. Seriously dudes! it actually looks great!

There is a 50 foot tall boulder here... this is not that boulder. But its a decent featured gently slabby face with cool undercling big foot crux near said boulder. Passed a lot of Mountain lion shit getting here. Next time I'm bringing protection. Condoms, yes.

BIG OL' slab right as you get to the first lake and a must do. Tried this a few times over the years but top quarter was way too dirty to force. Start in the center, and go through some easier nice moves to cruxy V1 moves using a crimp on the arete to get to the apex. The top is probably about 25 feet. There will certainty be a ton of great variations but this felt like the most prominent line.

AMAZING looking little lowball! Such a unique upside down moon shaped rock on the Mosquito-Mineral Ridge (Mineral facing face of boulder). Cool starting hold leads to a very odd mantley pop move that I have never done before. Obligatory belting of the Rick and Morty classic at the top.
One mover to the right of "The Clayboys? which is actually decent. Hard pull on and move to a good edge.

Multiple  year project 100+ tries. Literally only two moves which individual seem casual, but everything is so gory darn SOH PREH SAH DAH. Seriously! Even pulling on to put the heel is unlikely. I fell pulling on  so many times, not to mention pulling out! There is a good set of crimps I was unable to use so maybe an easier sequence is found but this was ALOT.
Same rad moon boulder, totally different climb. This is fun a lip traverse on the Mosquito side of the boulder. Aesthetics are so potent they made all the ladies in the first 3 rows pregnant.

Birthday Send Baby! Do all the things: 6:10 Mostra Coffee, 6:45 Frolf (-6!), 9:30 Beer 1, 10:00 surf, 11:45 skate home,  12:15 Beer 2-3 (Donut Box) + fruit, 1:00 yoga, 2:45 run, 4:00 Woodson Climb, 7:30 Food + Beer 4 + Friends + desert + Beer 5-10, 11:00 piano, 11:10 code, 11:30 duo lingo, 11:45 snuggle with Chooch. Fan-flipping-tastic day my dudes and dames! Thank you everyone! This climb has a nice hot slippery mantle.

I am TERRIBLE at time planning. I thought I could climb at woodson in 2 hours.  Lets break this down... 30 minute drive to + 30 minute hike in + 30 minute hike out + 30 minute drive home = plenty of time to climb. lolol. Tried Bowers Castle project but it felt impossible. Run with Jake was nearly as hard as the marathon, I'm a tired boy who needs beer. This think is Basically Problem A the right flake is off so you mantle direct.

Impossible to grade. I flashed any v6 or under climb i tried and did two "hard" v8s and this was harder for me than all that so I'm taking the OG v7 grade.  Using OG beta if you can pinch hard enough, every hold is a jug, but if you are like me and suck at gym climbing this feels hard. Such incredible features on this, hourglass pinch earns itself a nomination for greatest holds in America.  Thanks dwoo for making fun of my core and giving me hutzpah to send. You wise man dwoo.

Very my style. Weird yet powerful and vCool! Started right hand in lip pocket and right hand just above on the sidepull. Amazing how cruxy the monkey grip to meat hook flip is. Glad it wasn't named "black hole" definitely don't need any more boulders named that.  Dwoo only knows how to send if its part of a send train apparently. Also what the heck!? climbing with Dwoo in Alaska!? Unexpected and freaking awesome.  Kody be nice to this new baby setter!
What a July 4th! I wonder how many July Fourths I have climbed on? Time to consult david.vaskos.com. Stand start, did one shoe beta as suggested by balls. Nice quick stop.

This AK crew is amazing. DWoo, Hunter, Lisa, Me + Balls having a grand time. Literally feels like dudes and dames I've climbed and trolled with for years. Good times. This climb is that toke fucked up V3.  Not gonna lie hatcher pass may have just slipped into my top 5 bouldering areas... possible top 3... just wow.
literally 3 Davids out here today. A decent number. This climb is great and picturesque as hell. Well the whole valley is picturesque as hell and you can see the valley so yeah. nice.
Hunter got full on special sauced! Good fun.
Yes yes YES! So rad. Fun watching the crew flail like wet noodles on this thing lol.

Book give 9 probably for scare factor. Mucho  fun. another dwoo send train after he bruised his buttocks.  Had a few fun falls on this piece. I took a whip off the final jug with poor balls on spot. Double heels at one point, and hitting final jug is glorious.

Started LOW left on bad undercling and right on arete, quite dabby but fun. Crux bumps to AMAZING gritty sloper to an easy but kind of comitting top out. As a note to myself so i dont forge: Dwoo almost dropped his entire pack + pads into the lake rofl.

big left hand dead point to a tight heel. Not he most aesthetic of lines on this face but fun movement! The Vasko Voodoo project to the left looooks siiick (and dabby in a dang it hole) think of me if you try it Will!). 

Thank goodness for that Turning Point stop bc I got the goods! A 6pack of local golden ale and a six pack of a local citrus out the wazoo TIPA.

First time falling off the boulder... and it was a big fall too. Would have been my first AK FA, but the second GOOOO was one GOOO too late. Russ starting the choo choo. Fun climbing with cool crux from the obvious start jug across the face into the top of MVP gold. Could probably extend all the way to the arete.. may have to do that next time! Second Ascent. Good to have people to share beer with... although need to but cheaper beer for balls next time.

This is actually good, but felt hard and I may have started a move in. Wow. It took Russ more burns than Pistol Whipping so you know its soft. Maybe key beta makes the crux reach easier? Either wat that left hand crimp EATS your ASS, and by ASS I mean your left hand fingers. Sad i coulnt whip a pistol, but glad i was there to save Dwoos literal ass on his hero lauch out of the jug and sluuut.

The main obvious line up the back of the boulder from obvious just through obvious crack to finish. Again name MAY be off, just like bridge may be chocolate. Felt harder than 4,  but might just be because it was wet. Brussel Sprout really does look bad on top outs lol. He's seriously crazy strong so I enjoyedthis being the first climb I saw him on.

The Mother Lode boulder is RAD. Ooohhh Yeeah. Thanks again to Riley and Will for the spray down of these crags. Names are gonna be dubious here but this is my best guess until the guidebook comes out. Start both hands on the right hand start hold of "MVP Gold" and go through the cool edge.
The stand from the good edge is a great warm up!

Good highball, hard start techy top. Would be 5 stars but you can escape the direct start by SKIIIIRTING left. Cannot believe the gate closes at 7pm! good call will sending Russ yo get service and check. Ahhh yeahh. I WISH we had time to try the right exit, its literally called "Jean Luc Get Hard", if i knew that at the time i woudl have refused to leave until i got "Jean Luc Get Hard", Will you did good on that one. I will be back. Also who closes a gat at 7p m when its sunny until 2am?

Very short on time at this point! Only climb that I did that Dwoo did not (he would have if he tried), so byah! Everyone left me except BALLS, bc we needed to make that too early gate closure I mentioned earlier. Lisa had an amazing lead in where all my boys where dancing like the beautiful men they are but I BLEW it going for the jug next to the jug I should have gone for. Balls is a godo hiker and manteler, a match made in heaven. We need a matle off. A kiss has spit and fire and balls.

Second Ascent. Cody brings the psyche more than a woodchuck chucks wood. The middle line looked doable.. but was at least V11, the corner looked doable but was at least V10, the stand though did not sink into the swamp. One very fun move from a meat hook and small crimp to a jug. Cody also clashed "Destroying my master" which is pretty darn high on my next time list. Also he may actually name this.

Wonderful. I cant believe I can climb under the weather under the weather. It rained a bit today, and I feel a small cold coming on. You know I'm not well when I bring a 6 pack and drink none. This climb is good. Dont forget to massage your balls. Spot on is important for crux, be the leaf.

Literally blew the flash go turning around to tell Hunter "Yeah, of course Ill flash this, I like SQUEEZING". The turn popped my heel and I blew it everywhere. Settled for third go. Amazing squeezing with is detracted by the dab potentials.
Felt SOOO hard for me. Again on the same cool ripple feature but that cold is fffffing me. So many variations.

Yes im giving this 6. probably 5, but even with a dab it felt so hard. Wow. making ballz go low was nice. He doesnt go low. he went down for me. Kant believe I didn't Immanuel the even more left line.

Isaac starting the cold train! One of the few night Lisa slept better than me. Thought Caelyen would cruise this but then it cruised me and I re-thunk my thunking. Amazingly cool ripple feature. Great warm up wall.
Wow very nice. Trand Sap my dudes and dames. Great features  with good top
Fun! No pads needed. Just use the holds and dont fall.

A genuine party on this. Shout out Cody for his Fairy Tail tattoo and his One Piece hat. LOVE IT!. I love the little factoid from Ian that the friable block is indeed not friable and has claimed two crow bars lololol. Solid as hell that block. Fun moves on the sloper lip, will be better after some freeze thaws and that block falls.
On the flash go which I fully expected to send I rocketed outward right into balls. Russle's beta was quite nice, and allowed you to skip the sopping jug. Very fun movement good holds.
Wet dishes are still safe. Even with last nights wetness saturating live, I still flashed for the warm up. I am a good wet climber!

Was really hoping Will failed me and I could log this as "Wills Vagina"... oh well, Say Lah Vee. Ahh yeah. Broke a hold on my send. Dwoo epic. Good climb. Good group. Peace and love. I wonder how many Gorillas have been in paris. George of the Jungle is a fun movie. GOod job Lisa teaching Dwoo how to climb.

Almost pulled on, and would have surely blew the flash, but my dudes and dames were there to support me! Dwoo coming though with the send beta that worked for me, then didnt work for him, then suddenly the leaf came back and it once again worked for him. A crazy climb which is both hard and easy. Subtle as hell. Great climb, fin movemnt, good location, good landing. Must do for sure. Lisa crushing as we ditch her =P. Great work babe!
Would be good not wet. Aesthetic and good holds. Sopping like all tank girls should be.

The most single session burns I have given to something that actually went. Officially logging it as 34 attempts. Fingers are raw as hell. Said one more go maybe 11 times. Dwoo AGAIN starting a send train, CHOO CHOO. Those Dwoo train juices pulling me by the skin of my teeth. Literally stuck the dyno with a open handed lose the pinky catch. Wow. I made an "O" face for sure, just like lumbarg and Jennifer Anniston.

This ABSOLUTELY should have been my first V9 flash. booo. Too sick and tired of being sick and tired. Maybe a millimeter off from the flash. should have ticked. Good rec hunter, thanks for beta Russ, thanks for the chalk balls, and thanks for the support + footage Chooch! Next life. Nacho getting lute on the Pica hunt!
Wonderful. Like Pickachu on a stump. Worth the walk. Full of soft. The direct variation looks nice too and similar difficulty. Fantastic holds and movement.
So enjoyable! Wish Lisa was 100% bc she would have flashed.
It is nice. I'm sorry for passing the cold onto you Lisa. Boo. Now at least I have an area she doesnt! Muahaha
One of the best V2s out there. Perfect starting jugs, with interesting movement and its beautiful. BUT "Glacial Alchemy" looks even better! Next time.
Cool feature but pretty awkward.

This boulder is confusing. But there are some fun holds, some fun moves and some fun eliminates. This line has a very hard first move. I cannot believe how little psyche we have on climbing right now, its all about camaraderie you know. But no one wants a beer yet. Pretty oxymoronic you know. We are tired.
If you off route the entire big ledge at the beginning this actually feels like V4. Climbs enjoyably too even though that makes it insanely contrived.

mflash. I cannot believe the epic is over. Well I started matched on the right start hold for some reason, so maybe this doesn't count. A big ol' "Fuck" helped me stick the move to the good side pull. What a day.

What a whirlwind of a Day! Smoky as hell out in Bishop, literally 212 AQI whatever that means. Started with a lovely egg scramble made by the sweet chaseypoo then went straight into a  nice COVID scare. While at the Mammoth PCR testing site playing Hacky Sack with drew I saw chalk an a boulder. I climbed the boulder. Then miraculously, while flipping through the Mammoth Bouldering Guide later that day I happened on this very climb. wow. much.  Lets hope for -.

This day was quite the roller coaster. Full of wonder, surprises, boys, lethargy, beer, more boys, smoke, no smoke and against all odds, sends. Almost went to Sage to Summit to mMoonboard but thanks to the Covid scare we drove to the mammoth testing site and figured if there was no smoke we'd go to Lay Wake. There was no smoke. Feeling so weak but chase and I both somehow pulled with a classic pre send flail. Climbing is so weird. Maybe those low expectation lifted me like a fizzy lifting drink.
I was on this boulder back in 2014 but I never logged several of the lines and I log everything so I probably never did them. This start felt hard for 2 but maybe I started low.

Just wow. The craziness continues. Ran into so many people today, got more sends, and even gave a beer to Nate. We ordered Pizza but while waiting Chase mean mugged a dude who asked, "you want some" then he proceeded to give us 3 full uneaten pizzas, 12 uneaten wings and 20 uneaten breadsticks. I've been known to over order but never in all my years would I ever order 3 too many pizzas. Wow.  We pulled. Almost fell on the top.

What a lovely climb. Glad I flashed this bc Chase didn't, Grecian God of Shittiness at your cervix! But seriously, amazing crimps with fun moves, a jug midway, and a tenuous post jug crux. Glad I was there to save that man from spiraling to his doom. Also glad to find my Indian roots here, I had no idea. Also Shout out Marina for her inspiring send. Also shout out Pure Project for the rad celebratory quint!

I am regarded as a squeeze machine... but I sucked on this. I am not a body position machine though so that's my excuse. Once I actually positioned my body like a good boy it went smooth. For being a shorty this is so good.

Ouchie Mamma! Can I actually crimp now? I know I looked absolutely terrible but I did it right? AK said it was too heinous for him which gave me a big crimp ego boost... although he did do Crimp Ladder in the number of burns that I had sessions.  Sharp to where its almost not enjoyable. Do it quick or get fucked.

Shirley said I cannot put second go because I did Green Mamba. But I did this second try on this line so that counts for at least a few bonus points right Jens? Like Shirley said the secret was doing less. So many rad lines on this boulder. Shout out Ishmael for not being able to climb anything classically hard but being able to do all the hard projects. That on

Not very good. I topped out to the right so I could call it a flash only to remember that I warmed up on the holds out right. Then I remembered this is my logbook and I can do whatever the Fudgin Heck I want (as long as my sailors tongue doesn't offend anyone of course). Those bread crumbs and chases ingenuity made the discovery we needed to find this block and extend the trip one more day. Sorry Kody you will never climb here.

Careful 6-C-Plu will mess up your beautiful pyramid! Favorite line I did on the boulder but I could not do Freudian Dab and our group psyche plummeted so hard we didn't even try Chekov's, yet even with those caveats finding the eponymous boulder is a worthwhile adventure. The boulder didn't quite live up to my expectations but this is such a lovely spot wit nice water and trees. This particular climb has cool holds and movement. AK definitely dabbed on the tree topping out so no points.

Too bad we were all tired, Marina had to work and chase had to take his son to the vet BC sieging this boulder would have been sack.  This climb is almost cool but the flake you grab seems SO friable and really ruined the experience for me. Andy Liu used a heel on it but that seemed ludicrous. I used a high left heel instead which was quite cool. That all being said a magnificent trip and yes Scott you should be very very jealous. Always say yes to getting Sandy. Always.

I had long since given up on bouldering on Maui, but I guess things have changed and there are now some good secret local spots! Shout out Lisa for doing the research, rekindling the stoke and finding this micro area. Definitely wish we had a paddle board to get to some of the cooler looking lines, but still fun to fall a bunch. Couldn't get that sweet right line, fell gunning for the lip a ton. Glad I did this easy left line for New Area Metric.

I'm getting pretty excited to try East Clear Creek! DWS is so much fun. Lisa and I swam around to check out "The Backside" and it looked much chossier, more bird shitty than the front plus the water was a littlie to turbulent. So we didn't even try. My sincerest apologies goes out to the girl from the PNW who was inspired by seeing us climbng and got urchin-ed. Looked very painful.

Left Side of Black Rock. DWS grades are hard. Quite fun. Lisa being a bad ass and starting the back flip train. A couple guys were waffling and Lisa just says "If I do one, you have too" and nailed it. I was inspired and did my first back layout!

John giving me an amazing tour of his slice of the island. This beach Kahena is gorgeous and a plush nude beach. So many beautiful naked people, but I was too distracted by this rock to even notice. Cool movement, but some ridiculously friable chunks that could probably kill you. Make sure your ass looks good. This is the obvious cave at Kahena, start pretty deep.

Behind the obvious "cave" at Kahena there is a cool looking face. You can start sitting on some obvious jugs and work up and left through the big friable jug to gun for the sweet-as hold on the lip. Another with great movement but the big center jug will hurt if it rips.
Left side of the face start on an interesting complex of just and similar facing holds and do one hard pull off the ground to an easy top.

Looks like poop climbs better than that. Glad to be getting some rawness in these ol' tips of mine. Temps were good until about 10:30 when I because a roasted mess. I started with my hands at about head height, you could definitely start right hand one lower and do a hard hand heel first move.
Short but worth it for the feature alone. Apt name anonymous MP man name Colin. Literally a suspended fang. If I lay on my back beneath it it just barely touches my nipples.
Way easier than all other Woodson V3s, but enjoyable and I will relish my V3 flash.

I tried to sit start too far right on  the rail I think. The rail feature is rad but you wish you had more ass real estate. I think it definitely goes from the lowest holds but at probably harder grade. I started like three moves right from the mantle spot. Mantle is lovely and a little tweaky on the right leg.
I'm finally finding the good zeroes to show noobs! This thing is great. Short, flat landing with a jug at the top.

Climbs way better than it looks! And also way harder than it looks >.<. Those crux slopers are garbage until you find exactly where it likes to be caressed. Cool holds. Aden only gave this v3 on MP and I'm such a weak boy these days it probably is.

That's gotta be  my longest dry spells in quite some time! 39 days since touching real rock. Wow, quess thats why they call it window pane. I did television screen the OG way in 2015 but realized its an arete that can be done two ways so I did it leaning right, and I'm gonna tell you something. I liked it better this way.

PRNF: Definitely been done before but not on MP ill look at one of the old guides later. Cool large rock with a big ol pack man mouth missing. You can actually walk up to 15 feet height where you can do a very easy but a little scary mantle out of the mouth.
Decent slab. Figuring out the lay of the land today! Found two potentially undone lines that AB has known about for ages.

PRNF. Again could not find information.  Liebacking with interesting high step. Good ol' shattered beer bottles for the landing. A lower start may go, very cool arete feature low but the opposing flake is a hollow mess... maybe when it stops breaking. There is an amazing looking project on left side of this cool cave, at least V8.

PRNF. Grades at Woodson are impossible to assign, probably a Woodson V2. The landing and trail are human made, so in all likelihood this has been done before but I couldn't find any information.
