I thought Id cruise a few mantles on this but the only line I could do was the lip traverse which finishes on the "easiest" of three distinct mantles. There is a one move extension which will be ~V6 and the harder mantles def go. Named for the great audiobook I was listening to. Thx J Diamond and Libby!!

Decent little guy on the same boulder as Ox In Flight, west side of boulder, right side of the large crack. Sit start left hand on arete and right hand on an opposing hold low, a cool drive by move gets you to better holds. Somebody must have done this before.

I could not do the cooler lower start, but on the west side of the Ox in Flight boulder is some good jugs. Some of them are a little friable but a few fun warm up lines can be found. The best is this one which starts on the head high jugs and busts a big move up and left to better jugs.
Easier and not as good as the OG. Need more climbs to break my 2018 ascent count of 409. This climb puts me at 347 for 2021 so far.

Tough mantle! Looks like it should be easy but the steepness of the roof below sucks your right leg into oblivion. A xeno/crystal out left proved pivotal in getting my leg free. Literally stacked a few fingers on top of each other to slowly.. very... very slowly, pull yourself into the mantle.

This thing was way more fun than I expected. I thought one tough move into the fun top. But damn, first move is fire and the sequence to get into the stand, while not hard, is rad. This Ox Area is turning into quite a good are for some volume! Classic Woodson: if you want so send anything remotely hard.... come at night.
So many fun mantles I feel giddy as a school girl. This thing was unlike any mantle i have ever done... crazy body position to finally solve the puzzle.

Could honestly be v3. Each move is pretty darn casual but so gory damn delicate. Its so short but so technical and fun. Literally 3 sessions of slip and slide before I finally took. So glad there is a single opposing foot to make this doable bc quite fun.

Amazing big slab on the left of the approach trail on the way up. No idea the name and I don't dare propose one in these treacherous waters. Ridiculously easy but the rock is so cool. Def a few other lines on this including a cool mantle and arete variations.
Much wonderful this one. Tall and fun and easy.
Also much fun,  tall and a little harder than his partner in crime.
The east facing face. I started off some xenos then just walked up. Made sure to not touch the arete but line seems pretty vague. Would be harder staying further left probs. Good tall warm up

This one took me some work. And I couldn't even do it form the lowest holds. Heinous crimp move with bad feet, will be back for it though. Definitely gets pretty airy on this one, had to get to the crux many times to work it out both physically and mentally before I could commit. Climb safe my dudes and dames. Oh yeah and obviously the arete is off.

At the end of the ridgeline there are some absolutely massive rocks. Like so ridiculous. This is an easy flake on the big boulder before biggest baddest boudler which has the super inspiring but impossible looking overhang. Crux was the downclimb
Amazing and easy arete climb on the ridgeline after passing tombstone. Super easy but very fun.
This is just the coolest. So easy, but the feature is unreal. Literally a knife blade thin gentle arete with gets you pretty high off the deck. Might add this to my best VB list.
At one of the bigger switchbacks a just down into the valley a bit to do this little guy. One move from big crimps to the lip.
Good to be out here again! Nice climb. Makes a good warm up with The Arkenstone itself.

Will need to check with Aden on this one bc it probably had been done before but was too pointless, dabby and such to merit anything but a casual unnamed send. On the rock to the right of Arkenstone, where I set up my camera there is a jumble of rocks and in between the jumble is a slanted ledge. The ledge is a pretty cool feature and would be rad if there wasn't a rock directly behind it but you can force an easy dabby line.

The choss is gross, but it does have fun moves! Started at the lip of the cave with my hands, and my feet deeper in on a cool array of holds a few newtons from breaking. The crux DP is quite a lovely red point crux.

Yes I am logging this twice which is unfortunately gonna move it to the top of the 8a list alongside Ante Meridien where this does not belong (because it will have 3 ascents). The reason for the second log is because I found a lower start that wasn't any harder, but was even more enjoyable! Start on the "fin"-ish feature in the middle of the cave and pull into the same line as the OG. A knee bar may make some chossy but delicious magic happen.
Very fun first move. I Bang-On'ed it, but I think the FA-ers dis a big gastony move.
A lovely cleaved face. Short but as a seasoned pebble wrestler this brought me great joy. Small crimp high foot lock off baby.
Def worth doing if you are out here. Cool pinches and body position get you up this shorty.

This was wildly fun, and certainty makes a trip out to Proprioception even more worth it. Feels almost like comp slab problem with interesting body position, hard foot moves and practically nothing hand holds.

How wonderful. This is a very cool textured face (like its a big marble layer or something on top of the granite but there is splotches of granite on top of that too!) . This has good edges and nice movement, with crux reach to the lip. Sweet as! Aden was out here today and I finally got to meet the dude! I saw his IG post as I was headed to LR myself, woohoo.

Unlike anything. Keep in mind that I basically never trad climb so of course I would never normally wedge my bottom half as deep in a hole as possible then wriggle my way slowly sideways while staying 6 inches off the ground. If that doesn't sell it, that because this climb is more of an experience than a boulder problem and experience, my friends, is algorithmically incompressible. Pretty sure you could lie back it... but that is not fun. Invert and work on those shin muscles!

A variation on Proprioception. Mantle straight up/left from the starting crimps. I'm always amazed how often mantles surprise me with their subtle uniqueness and difficulty. This one had me completely chaarmed and took a lot of skin, energy and at least 30 tries. From the subtle name I'm sure you have guessed that with a lack of down pulls I was forced to use a very high thumbdercling.
fun little guy. good hacking grounds.

Had the most amazing explosion off this climb. Going for a nice padless ascent and absolutely rocked off those last crimps. My cat like agility saved me from anything serious, and a lovely full bodied laugh from Chase let me know it was all worth it. Only a few beers deep at the time. It was gnar. Got back on the pommel horse and cruised it having found the correct foot and sans grease fires.
tis good. my beers keep spillin

Wow, I am so thankful for the many wonderful people in my life, as well as many wonderful beers. Great extended Thanksgiving weekend with Shirley, Winifred, LIB, Mr Ludwig, Kodi the Dog, Kody the Man and a short splash from Drew and Jamie as well as a quick session with Aden! Perfect condies for Boudners 6 Premier! I don't hate my fingers, this things is soft, but the first move is entertaining. The wind blew over like 3 of my beers today... grumble grumble grumble.

Probably been done before but a cool link up of Gypsy's Day out into Gypsy's Arete. Do the first move of Gypsy's Day Out (left hand way) then do a big move out right to join Gypsy's arete. Had to finger lock but the move out right and heel throw was much enjoy. So windy, literally (almost literally) no one else out at black today. Glorious. Except that gory darn wind of course. Honestly surprised we didn't see any trees fall.

Kody, I did this one! Easier that Big Greenie, but rad crux to the honker. Goo goo ga ga mommy! Great view and landing is really not bad at all. Just get a half decent not drunk spotter. Really should be done more with how close this is to the main area.  A little but of crumbles but if it gets the traffic it deserves that will all roll off.
Campus Mantle to the left of Finger Hate. Trying to break my all time record for climbs in a single year so expect more of these ultra test pieces.

What a nutty climb. If you loved the spice on Mega Ghost or All Alone Together, this rig is for YOU! Start on an underling jug to the right of Mega Ghost and set up for a radical swing whose trajectory is directly at the chasm. Im pretty sure you would hit the landing rock first, plus its a jug, plus Im an athlete so nothing to worry about.  Finish via a large move up and right continuing thru some more crazy huecos. Not sure if it was bc i was a few beers deep, but the swing scared my Mr Ludwig. Would be MEGA if not for dab potential. Thx kody for getting me on this.

I wonder how many times I will get to re-send this climb as holds keep breaking! Loved my beta this time around. Never once touched the slopers on the right: first move as normal, then out left to the flake, then hand heel matched on the right for an awesome perch that took me all the way to the classic pinch. Tried to rush send this to save some time for my crew on the walk down and had to settle for mssg. No wine today my dudes and dames. Does feel noticeably harder for V7 post break.

This thing was quite good for how little it gets done. Plus the view is top notch. Just don't drop your hackey sack off the cliff on accident. Lovely features, fun moves and  topped with a cherry of a mantle.

Kody this climb will likely fall into obscurity because the name has no soul. I mean Lower NRA is rad and it basically never gets done. This thing is surprisingly wonderful. More amazing features with fun moves. That starting xeno is beyond pleasurable. Seems cray that a whole climb fits to the left of "Lower NRA" but it does!
I knew if this ever went it would go with my boy Kody the Man. Pretty sure I broke the good lords intended beta, but I got to the top so ill take it.

Kody give this a name so I can correctly log. In my head the hard thing to the left had "wizard" in the name so that's why I have it logged like this. Hard heel placement and slap to a rather enjoyable serving of arete compression on great rock quality. The stand is a good problem in its own right. So tired and sore, warming the booty up is rough.
My shoulder skin and thigh skin is so raw... those pineapple shorts were not ideal for Gregs Crack.....
hot and greasy. the way it was intended.

Good fun with a start studded cast today! I suck at crack so was not willing to do Monkey Crack despite Ben and Eric making it look casual, but I could do this thing. Hard first thrutch to a nice easy mantle.
Fooling around with Jed, Aden and the crew. Eventually I settled on this thing which has a bad landing and friable looking xeno knobs, but hey.. crux was a fun drive by to a jerggg.
PRNF: Just another unnamed Woodson slab just off the road on the right passed Poison Oak Crack. Pretty obvious and probably V0, but it was enjoyable.

Wow I thought I would feel good with a few rest days under my belt but I guess the quality or rest days is important. Two nights of super drunj is NOT good for recovery.  My skin was still raw and wet from the 4 days on over thanksgiving if you believe it. I really thought I would have a chance at maybe SNAFU or Together Apart but that was quite unrealistic. So, I did this silly link up and I thought it might be cool but in reality it definitely detract from both halves. On another note there might be a shitty low to Edo Tensei. All depends on if its possible to leap into gastoning choss from full extension.

Almost really cool, but a few holds feel gross and its a wee dabby. The movement is wonderful though and good top holds. The book is silly in its start description, the obvious line starts in the side pull jug and patina crimp. No chase i could not do Vulgarine, so out of gas and the sweaty sausages were in prime form. Poon star looks fun. Solo trip today was so exhausting. I did scope a bunch of yellows tho.

It is my style but, with how bad I felt, I should not have flashed V7 with lubricated ease. I am surprised how few ascents this has, its a rad feature. Wanted to try the sheer face of love but honestly i lost motivation, rarely happens to me. I did take a rad spill while carrying my two pads and banged my knee pretty good. that and my tiredness was really draining.

Might b V2, but I topped out to the left instead of rolling onto the slab which certainty added some difficulty. This boulder is one of the best I've been to in at Woodson (South) in terms of quantity on one boulder!
A very nice mantle. Simple, easy but pure.
Looks derpy but actually packs in an enjoyable mantle!

The AWESOME arete on the right side of the big slab that is the 67 Boulder. Unlike clif_crab, I thought the more natural start was starting on the left side of the Arete: Mr Crab did a move of two leaning right then transitioned onto the slab. I think similar grade either way, I want to do it all the way up on the right side but gotta clean up the choss and the landing is scary.

Unsure of grade, my initial thought was V5 but I am good at squeezing and crux sloper is garbage. Start on your ass on below the arete with right hand on a slightly underclinging crimp super low and left hand on the sloping lip where it feels natural.
Why is the texture of this rock so amazing!?  as good as lip traverses get. Thanks AJ for the reccomendation!

Start on two good holds on the lip at the very center of the incredible slab of the 67 Boulder. Pull a wonderful mantle then smell the roses as you enjoy some beautiful slab moves up the center of the glorious and tall slab. Grade is ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ Reference is to one of the best American "amines" ever.
One of the most obvious crack as south woodson. So good.
Another ridiculously AMAZING easy climb at south woodson. An easy lie back in a beautiful and massive dihedral. The arete on the right side of the dihedral definitely goes and will be fantastic.
Started on the same start hold as Baby Oak which improves IMO, adds a cool move out left to get to the crimp you mantle on. Improved mantle beta makes this not too hard

Apparently V4 is my default grade lol. Probably easier. This climb is on the East side of the big boulder just before the 67 Boulder. It really should start one move lower than I did, but it was surprisingly hard. I did a jump start to the flat rail and bounced on come gastons to work my way up. THe start move is going to be SUPER good when it goes.
This thing is just high enough to wet your pants a little. Landing is amazing tho so thats good. What a striking arete. Pulling off the ground is the hardest move but keep your wits about you!

This climb is super close to the Call Box Parking. Like two minutes up this is on your right, start with left hand on a big side pull feature, and right hand like 7 feet height on a PERFECT full pad in cut crimp. I wish it was possible to start one move lower be cause latching that bad boy would be loot.  Pull on and do a harder than it looks top out, its pretty insecure and landing is not the best.

This gets stars in basically every category imaginable. Location, check! Movement, check! Holds, check! Aesthetic, check! Tops a Jug, check! This boulder is literally on top of another boulder on the summit, so cool. This is very crimpy and as such felt WAY harder to me than most other V6s. I did break 2 feet some while working the moves, but didn't change anything

Super cool separated patina flakes with a height that creeps up on ya. I broke two feet, one of them which was used in the original crux beta, so i think its a tad harder now. I had to basically campus my feed up from the high right down pull and the sloper out left. Very fun movement.
So fun but sadly such surprisingly bad rock quality. I was working a low start and it was a blast. Cant wait to go back and put it together!

This line is one of the best on the mountain in my opinion. Quality rock, rad holds, fun movement, perfect height,  and a beautiful location. Remember the first time I saw this like 8 years ago and wanted to do it but its rather intimidating. Hard as shit for V6, feels surprisingly endurance-y for a ~8 move climb. Tried the top on TR a week or so and was confident I could pull. Thanks Kristie for the extra pad, support and footage. Great job hiking out here, climbing and breaking in that beautiful new pad. With this I've tied my all time ascents in one year! Woot!
Kind of a hard start, my foot hilariously blew on a pre send flail. This boulder had such amazing rock quality. Love it.

It might be possible to start on the two edges (which seems like a more obvious start) but it felt miserable with no feet. Get the left foot up and then simply tic tac up your hands taking care not to blow the foot. I cant believe how bad that good left foot feels.

Wow I didn't realize I forgot to log this despite being an FA? How is this possible!? I guess I had too much fun to remember a silly mantle with a awkward landing. Only realized I missed this when I was reading through the Lake Ramona Guidebook today, 20220115, and saw a climb named "David's Mantle" and wondered what other FA Mantle Silly boy also named "David" Aden was cheating on me with. lolz. I guess it was me the whole time.

Surprisingly good for a jump start to slopers. Although, I think I kind of like jump starts. Glad to have Aden today to throw me on anything with a mantle =D. A little sad that the 8a name is not "Beef Wellington Deja Vu"... Deja Vu is fine I guess.

I don't know why I think this climb is so cool. Its literally a first move campus crux on painful holds. Somehow despite that ugly surface, its warmth and tenderness really shines through. You will have to do it yourself to understand. Also, how can you possibly see a lake in the backdrop of every climb here. Lol. Did it with Jeds original beta, these monkeys who can do the ring lock campus are just bananas.

Bring out your Jugs! Bring out your Jugs! Wow the start of this thing has jugs in spades if that makes sense. When the jugs run out you can either mantle there for an easy V0 or continue to the apex on the lip with a rather tenuous  V1 move! Great addition Aden!

I love climbs with aesthetics and this thing is basically a Michelangelo. I also love that the reference is to "A Bugs Life"! So rad. The fact it can be climbed is a nice bonus too. Just a pure mantle my dudes and dames.

Easier, reachier variation of Hulk Smash Low.  If you have the span you can reach a good but friable hold far out left which makes the move to the starting pinch of Hulk Smash significantly easier. The hold feel solid-ish and may survive a few seasons but it might just rip next burn, who knows. That being said pretty unique movement for LR. Very overhung and powerful moves. The holds are rad and sequence is crazy fun with some cruxy rips. Make sure to catch you rip grunt on camera! Really want to come back a little stronger and do Aden's version!

Very good, would be incredible but its too short! Perfect press into under cling . Also did the "left" exit which is also worth doing, and part of what makes this little area such a good warm up spot. What a Joyous day climbing with Aden and Greg... well except the COVID part... that was not joyous... sorry boys.

It no longer seems as rare as it once did, but a lot of the big flakes that fall come off have cute lizards inside. The guilt you feel about destroying such a cute creatures home is absolutely crushing. At least I didn't send them plummeting dozens of feet lol. Anyway use some magic energy to do a very mantle-ey thing to reach some crimps. Delicately dance your feet until you can stand up and reach the lip. Needs some more cleaning, but could gain a star if it cleans well. Aden this is my name for "David's Face"

Needed to see Aden cruise it before I could realize the truth: it was soft all along. A short shorty but the one move is entertaining. The more problems in this little warm up cluster the better! Just pull apart and enjoy that soft-sweet-sticky ness

V2! Man I suck. Upgrading. It is definitely good n techy with "just too bad" hands  and "just too bad" feet to be easy. Start holds are a little dubious, so I started fairly high; any lower would be harder. Basically one high step gets you to better holds. I did not have to yar on the paper cut hold, I was able to bump my right hand all the way to the good opposing feature.

Place holder name until Greg comes up with something. This is the V0 choss pile to the left of "Tug of War" Honestly not bad movement but too much choss to be good.... yet. Was just gonna log as "Greg's Chosspiece" but I didn't really want another climb with "choss" in it to accidently stick. When I pulled up an image there is a pretty obvious "S" on the boulder, so wanted to reference that.
Very obvious and very good. I suck at crack. Does it ever stop hurting? Guys? guys..?

Took me a impressive number of burns. Some of the movement was very subtle and until I put my foot in the right place I kept peeling. Another vey high start, but this one is obvious. Rad sequence on a cool feature

This is gonna be one of those "be honest and take the grade you deserve" climbs. For example, for Drew go-go-gadget-im-a-plus-seven he might honestly be able to span form the start jug all the way to the good down pull. He might not even consider this class 5. However someone less than 5 feet either cant do it or it would be hella hard. I was able to skip a match Aden had to do which is why I'm giving it 6 (range is probably v5 - v8 depending on lank). Crazy fun unconventional awesomeness. Only giving three starts but it is still a must do and I think once the crowds start pouring in it will become an area favorite.
After this I'm ready for the rest of hueco! Actually quite a fun big move from jergs to jergs

So close to a recommend. I didn't really like the first two moves, but then the rest is as good as Iridium Start Fruit wine if you know what i mean. Stardew Valley is such a good game. ConcernedApe is one of my heroes. But yeah back to the climb, the last few moves are perfect grips perfectly spaced with rad moves between.

A wonderful time. Nice meeting Mr Winkler here today. We literally have the same pad set up:  A big organic with a send blubber inside and a send Saddle Bag. Classic combo I must say. I like that Mr Winkler recognized that I was "The guy with Covid" from my evasive remarks lol.
Hueco has "huge tracks of land" if you know what I mean. Features oh my gooodness oh my goodness oh my god! Yeah super enjoyable and I loved my heel above hands beta.
Pretty much perfect for a face V0. Lovely bullet edges on a clean face.

Nuttin like testing positive for COVID the night before you are supposed to drive out! Woot woot! Send the boys off in the Great White Whale packed tight with crash pads . It was rather lucky we were carpooling bc otherwise there would have been no foam for our group. I thought my Grecian Godliness would heal me instantly but I was testing positive for so long. Finally drove out and stayed in a separate AirBnB than the sick one I booked for the group and climbed solo at North my first day. I'm glad for beers in the back yard and at least one night marinating in the tub.
What a classic first ever climb in hueco.
I did not like this. Also very hard. Started below the sloper.
Book tells me this is V7. Apparently you can go feet first which makes sense in retrospect. Fin feature is all time.

Holy fuck I did not expect that. Post COVID bod got me low on energy so figured id check out this 4 start V2. This climb is perched at the end of a narrow slot canyon that drops down to the front side. You can even see it from the road if you have your glasses on. Amazing jugs and crazy cool crux to get out from the overhang onto the hueco loaded top. I did it an cruisers sans pads and was not really mentally ready for the tall top. Luckily its jergs. Damn son.
I enjoyed myself a little more. Rad as hell holds on the martini roof. Features for days. Drew is a funny boy when he cant do something.
Such a nice boy.

This roof is so steep it might be down climbing! Amazing that such a steep roof is only V4, that's how you know the holds are big. Rad 3d movement, rather tiring and not the best warm up for sure. Drew bang-on-ed the start move and it looked rad.
Took me like 9 tries to get my ass off the ground then took it to the top. Effing hard first move but loved the rest. My steeze.
So un-hueco-ey, but very fun! A puzzle, a scholar and a saint. Took more burns, and skin, than I wanted to spend but i got sucked in. My beta used a satisfying lurtch for the lip.
More warm ups. Yay for climbing with friends! Excited to wear a N95 all day!
I honestly liked this better than King Kobra. Pressing AND squeezing on the same boulder?! Me likey.
That was nice... i enjoyed myself.

felt impossible to pull off the ground and then it went. I enjoyed faking a desperation grab to the loose undercling just to make scott shit in his own mouth. Bad rock quality for the top is a real bummer.
Worth it for the sloper feature alone. Rode that kneebar with the three little piggies all the way home.
warm ups baby. Drew is still a funny man.

Most enjoyable barefoot climb I have ever done: I even did a barefoot toe hook for the first time! So soft this would have made a nice V9-flash candidate but oh well. Big shout out to our Boy Ned for pulling his first V9 flash on a ludicrously impressive flash of "Better Eat Your Wheaties"!

Add that to the amazing send trains with Woo, Woohoo choo choo my dooooood! If he hadn't sent I wasn't even planning on trying again. Woo also saved my ass by coaching me into smarter top out beta. Loved the bottom shoulder moves.
A dab here, a dab there. Dodgson, Dodgson, we've got Dodgson here! See nobody cares. Nice hat.

The sun is a mass of incandescent gas
A gigantic nuclear furnace
Where hydrogen is built into helium
At a temperature of millions of degrees
Points points points! Jergs to big move to slightly tricky top.
That was a lot of logging. I seriously should get a good lumberjack outfit to do this next time. This climb was decently fun with a nice big move and then some good tension. Hard for four for sure.
I heard this is V6 now. Makes sense. Cool low moves, not as great top.
nothing interesting funny or dumb to say here. le sigh.

I wish I would have done the multi pitch version of "Big Nose Milley" but standalone will have to do.  I feel like a broken record but ill say it anyway; cool features! Heuco must have a lot of features i guess. I read this well... or I read this good. One of the two.

Absolutely should have flashed but it just too dark in this hole. Groping in all the wrong places. Pleasantly surprised with how much strength has returned after the rest day. Fuck COVID everybody, fuck it. 66 V points today... so close to classic.
Kinda fun. Def easier the more lank you have. Had a full on one handed iwo swing on the undercling. Had to mustard hard to hold on.

Rained out yesterday, hoping to go to East today but we were not the primary so we went where they wanted to go, which happened to be somewhere we wanted to go but not now and apparently they didn't really want to go here either since none of them sent this or even tried the feather... interesting. Very very interesting. Good guys the lot of em, but curious. Also found Paul Winklers water bottle from last season on the scramble up in a crevasse. I mean what are the odds!? This climb is gorgeous and climbs pretty well too, and hard. Sorry I didn't catch you on that flash go Woo.

I gonna indulge myself here and bump this 7/8 to 8. Not because its V8, oh goodness no, simply because doing so is bringing me joy. This was my favorite climb in Hueco, and in order to save time I committed myself to flashing. If only we didn't have that confusion about "why are we even at the feather" Woo may have had enough time to rest properly to dispatch (the feather). That being said, I had mentally rehearsed the moves to this thing many many times: all 22 of em! I was so ready you would have thought I'd been born at this boulder. Perfect pockets and jugs lead to crux 1, then you set up on a gaston and high heel and find yourself in the red point crux! Derek tells me 5 more inches for like 20 inches before I snag the jug. Totally exhausted I managed to mantle and stand on top of this massive block. Jump downclimb boys.

Definitely not the correct climb, and dont really know how ill find the correct one so eenie meenie miny mo for the win.  The climb I am logging is the cool V1/2 in lower forest near Pyro Isykys. Very nice jugs with slightly technical top out. If new information comes to light i promise i will correct my log book.
Crack is wack.

Very nice. Some sub par rock quality removes some stars but amazing opening huecos lead to a technical crux and a heady finish! Nice job pushing through this one Emma! Speaking of which, awesome meeting you: you were an awesome addition to our sandy crew!! Just the right amount of asshole and douchebag.
Best in the corridor... but also not really even sure if this is the right name. Close enough for government work. Big crux first move
Decent face with one really good lock off move and some quality dab potential at the top. Too many pads and people for this small corridor!
Looks a little dumpy but surprisingly interesting movement earns this bad boy the coveted recommend. Seems the correctly spelled name is "Pyro Iyskys".
No way the name is right on this one either. This one has the crimp you can hang one of those wooden crimp me things on.

Based on the descriptions I am guessing this is correct. The amazing Highball that Albert recommended kind of between 'Best of the West' and 'The Feather'. Me an Caleb ran up and boy did I feel like a giddy little leprechaun ascending to my treasurtabation material. Accidentally dropped poor little totoro off the top and thank god he didn't pull a "Paul Winklers Water Bottle" and dive into a crevasse.
First go but shares holds with "Head Face". A nice bucket jug makes this appealing, but the dabber rock to your right removes most of that appeal.

I love how supportive Albert is, no matter how horrible the beta I come up with he still supports me. What a man amongst men. Seriously he is a wonderful guide! No drop knee for me, just lock the left heel in and keep bumping left all the way up!
Doesn't get much better than this. Crazy and awesome rip crux. Loves the top out moves too. Speaking of love, I also loved the juggy beginning too. And speaking of speaking of love.... Scott?

I am a wasteland of exhausted particles piled into a human shape. Very sad I couldn't put a cherry on top of my trip by pulling "try harder" shoutout Woo for making miracles happen. Sorry for derailing our "how the fuck did we just send train that" V9 send train train. Anyway, at least flopped my ragged, wobbly inflatable, BRF limbs up this thing. Looked my style and soft but I fell on this thing more times than the amount of nights we had pasta.
Wonderful move off the wee gaston. Again Albert I hear what you are saying, and your points are valid, but I'm going to ignore your voice and use the heel. I love that Woo likes that movie too <3.
Lovely and hard. Its great that THE benchmark can be "hard" lol. That first move is a lot for a boy like me. But at least I'm not in a blender.

Emma told me I just had to grab the penis like I've been practicing every night since I turned 6 but it felt easier to just bump bump bump bump bump! Sorry for breaking a crimp on this with my wild heel hook betas. Also sorry spotters for saying whoops on the top out.
Why is this thing so hard? Amazing jergs lead to not jergs. Jeeze louise.
I had a dream once... ceramic unicorns and all. This is a juggy rightward trending feature made of the most kitty litter like quartz I have ever seen.
obligatory.

Oh boy what a let down. I explored this area off the 8 Freeway (32.664714, -116.210682). We saw it on our way to Hueco and I was so stoked I went to explore shortly after getting back. I cant believe it but this place makes Joshua Tree look like bullet. Literally everything is shit. I could rub holds off with my fingers and every flake felt like paper.  There were a FEW sections of a darker patina (kinda like JTREE) that had promise but never a dense enough section to merit climbing. I'm sure somewhere out here there is a good cluster of good rock... but damn... This climb was some big through huecos in the wash behind one of the big boulders. At least I got to visit the clothing optional facility!

I'm glad Aden and his phone are okay. Both took a spill off the same filming rock. Surprisingly they fell at different occasions. I felt bad bc I had him set up the tripod with HIS phone instead of mine then it blew over lolol! I wish I could give this climb 5 stars because it is very inspiring but  a reachy move and some choss detract from it. That being said it is absolutely a must do for ~highball fans at LR.

Recommend and Star whore over here! Sometimes my brain convinces me that just being climbable merits 5 stars, too many endorphins firing in the ol' noggin I think. That being said, for a lil guy this thing was quite fun, cool holds and good moves!
The big foot ledge makes it p-easy rolling right. Would be dilp do do without the foot ledge! Just slapping up roundness!

Thank the lord for glory temps. Always avoided this boulder bc it bakes, but blistering winds and moderate cloud cover baby, thats a different story baby. Aden loves those bubbly ripply features, and ill admit, they are pretty cool baby. THe new lower start looks radder.
Get use to it... yes I log everything, even this borderline hike/climb =P! Across from decimation there is a detached flake block that makes a easy 6 foot tall proud ass climb.

This thing would honestly be the Dilpness without the back dabber rock! Might be moveable? hike a Car Jack out anyone? Would probably be easier too. Start sitting to the left of Hotsy on a big right hand undercling/sidepull and the lowest of the left and opposing feature. Slap once and dont dab (crux!) then continue right and top out on the big feature that would kill you if it ripped out.
Sometimes you need it, but most times... you don't. Start in some form of compression to the right of Pit Stop like 8 feet. Slap once or twice then top out.
Great day out with Aden! Having fun in the Row doin funky moves. What a lovely name =P
V4 did feel more fare, if this is even the correct line I'm thinking of. Cool flat ledges. Another hard start move. I made the crux easier but more enjoyable by being fat and ripping a hold cheers!
What a perfect easier mantle! Perfect foot with a natural flip-a-rooni.
This thing is just too sick. All the holds are good, it moves well and tops a jug. Oh the view is rad too! Best V3 at LR so far that I've tried!

Just the STAND. Hard to grade bc: (1) I'm weak, (2) the wind was whipping making the non-existant holds feel like velcro (3) the move is super weird. Really fun though and will be back for the low. Looks like enjoyable moves into the same balancy crux!

I know I'm fat, possibly facing long term covid (I haven't been sore from a hike since my first time in the third grade), rarely climb and normally such at crimping but damn this thing reminded me of all those shitty things. Seriously pulling on took all my might! Dont even ask about pulling out. Because dont, there is some serious choss to your right and up top. Rad reach THO.
I think this is the correct name? Aden? The climb to the left of Pit Stop. Some cool top holds but there is a middle move that is just eww.
Yee quite odd indeed. Cool undercling-y pinchy block like thing on the arete
More weirdness coming at you. Start the same but transition to the left side of the arete on that cool pinch block feature ish thing and finish up that way.
Cool big move to honker jug, and choss =D.
Looks like it might climb trivially, but a ends up being a tad technical! Cool concave feature with a enjoyable press to navigate into the glorious underling.

One of those climb names you are a little worried to Google... lol. Very enjoyable moves with the sensual hole in exactly the place you want it to be. Did it from a sit which adds an enjoyable mantle into the starting scoop. Don't think it changes the grade but its nice.

The Cataclysm feature never ceases to amaze me. This climb is the long traverse on "the other half" of the Cataclysm boulder. Start as far left as you can and traverse right all the way (thru the hollow feature unfortunately) and top out once you hit the scoop.

Oh how lovely. The features make this thing. Start right hand on the left breast and left hand in a jug side pull.  Move up and left across the face via a large reach to the incredible side pull features. A little contrived, but movement wise very enjoyable and worth doing... even if just to cop a feel ;)
The left arete/ flake thing on the Exquisite Breasts Boulder. Some serious choss down low, but as you ascend you get to that good good bullet.
This is why "Exquisite Breasts" is contrived, exiting right onto the slab is too easy. That being said, our entire sport is contrived so just enjoy the movements that the rock gods give you.

This is a shoutout to Aden, the loving father and caretake of LR. He's not the hero we deserve, but he's the hero we need. Not sure that quote applies here but anytime I think the word hero saying that is obligatory. Aden literally would have left the sit to the amazing mantle undone if I truly desired the FA. No ego at all, hats off and mucho respecto to you good sir. This climb is a short face to the left of that short cool scoop mantle thing. Start on the obvious right facing jug and just work up.

Another one that climbs so wonderfully despite being a little short! Nice to get these good good recs straight from the LR source. Great feeling rail leads to the insecure, but satisfying final reach.

Lordy Lord. Movement wise this thing is one of the better V1s anywhere, buuuut choss gods are not so kind. Oh landing gods must have been a little cantankerous too. Start no hands in the orifice and exit the concavity by following the jug seam up and right until you can reach the crux down pull, lock off to another honker jug and smile. If you have a Void Ghost Pendant maybe you can have this cute little roomate move in?
yes this is a lowball, but the scoop is just so obvious it begs to be climbed. It would be an amazing finish move to a 10 foot climb, but alas its only like 4 feet tall.
Honestly pretty good but the choss out left certainly detracts.
That silly jug starting choss jug foot lol. More good high stepping on them shallow pockets!
In za sticky stickY cruisahs mahn! More nice mantleing  at the LR

Wowzer!!! Cant believe I had not looked at this feature before! The low is a squeeze piece! I wanna get back in shape and see if I can start even lower than Aden! Located perfectly between the two towers and usually has coveted temps. The stand is a very gymnastic arete with good holds and a slightly insecure final stand. A little grainy but very very good. Not in the sun which is just the best.

Start on the right side of the Stardew Valley arete and pull some interesting tick tacs on some not quite good holds. I ended up finishing up left into the "Stardew Valley" finish but pretty sure you can wrap right if that feel easier. On the send I didn't see a few holds that should make a little easier, so I think this should settle in at V4.

I think I am officially re-addicted to this game... =D. Also ConcernedApe is one of my heroes. This climb can be found down hill from "Trypophobia" toward the rich people. Climb the obvious corner by mantleing into the scoop, and doing one compress-ish reach on the arete to a "probably solid" jug. Another high mantle spices the finish! Channing to V2 after re-evaluating and comparing difficulty of climbs close by.
Its a mantle to the right of Sharpest Lives. Mantle straight, don't use the big thing out right. Yes cruises are posseeblay

Aden walked up this thing but it was anything but nice and easy! True slab moves. Pretty sure I wore out my new instincts in record time, they cannot hold an edge for bananas! Cool subtle features and wee pockets!

Doesn't look incredible, but climbs just so! Super rad pocket holds and a dearth of feet set up for the meaty crux! I ended up finding different beta than Aden ( I blame my flaccid instincts), but equally cool!

This climb is actually good, so I had a very real internal struggle finding a worthy name I could be happy with. But then I asked myself, what do I love? I immediately thought of all my waifus: Winry Rockbel, Saber, Erza Scarlet, Asuna, etc etc and realized this climb deserved to be in that echelon. In case you don't know: 'Waifu' is a term for a fictional character, usually in anime or related media, that someone has great, and sometimes romantic, affection for. Is it possible to have romantic feelings for a rock? Think about it. This climb is on the south side of the Half Moon boulder and start like 7 feet up on a perfect mantle feature; another sloper feature up and right makes this all time. Plus the views from here are just breathtaking. Aden and I both eat mantles for breakfast so if consensus thinks V4 I would not be sad.

Such different style than the stand, but the stand is only enhanced by these lovely crimp rails. Aden thinks probably closer to V5 but this felt like the hardest thing I did all day by far. Granted it was hot, I suck at crimping, and I am fat right now but I stand by V6. Glad I finally remembered send beers to celebrate this lovely addition to LR.
That's a tough V1 dyno! V-Fun though.
This boulder is quite chossy but has some nice large holds to do things with. Start same a Ape Index but move left and up

Possibly V5 when not in the sun but a fairly difficult press regardless. Directly opposite "Turtle Shell" there is a pretty obvious sloper that begs to be mantled. I could have stacked pads, but it felt pretty more fun as a jump start to some slightly better slopers on the right side of the slopey feature. Loud slaps and outta the pool get you outta the pool.
Start on the rad start hold of "Starscream" and ruin that line by moving left and sucking away all the fun.

An nice rock onto your foot move makes this rather nice. The weird concave feature is cool.  Even though it adds no difficulty I though sit starting with right hand on a juggy undercling added some length and enjoyable factor.

Lip traverses are notorious for looking silly, but every few hundred millennia, evolution leaps forward. Thanks Dr Jean Grey. That being said this lip traverse is really as good as it gets: wonderful sloper holds, surprisingly good and aptly placed feet, good and pretty obvious finishing mantle. I held out doing this one bc good conditions are pretty rare and it gets hit by sun most of the day but glad I finally put my greasy sausages on this rig.

Movement wise this thing is quite wonderful! I lost some wind from my sails seeing how chossy some of the rock looks, and if it seemed like you could probably lie back the jugs if there wasn't rocks in the landing, BUT if you don't show up for the new spiderman movie with unreal expectations it will certainly be amazing. A good lesson in expectations this boy. Come and climb it the way god intended and enjoy that rad rad sweet sweet crux sequence.
Doesn't look like much and kind of under the brush, but moves well and the features are cool. The large foot shelf is very nice.

Dang. Harder than I expected, but that happens with one movers! Its quite sad this climb is so short because the starting edges are so wonderful and the sloper jug is all time. Certainly a must do lowball at LR

Oh my lovely! A pretty line that climbs equally pretty. I feel pretty, oh so pretty, oh so pretty and witty and technical! Did it from a sit but the stellar moves are up higher. Such a perfect little scoop for your right hand sets up that high crux! PS the downclimb is not cake

I am very happy with how this turned out. It is a contrived line as moving left from the start hold is V0, and I was able to exit early via a mantle at two separate places (the mantles were scarier and possibly harder than the full line), but the holds are stunning and feel so cozy for your chalky mitts. Start on an obvious juggy edge and move right through another juggy complex to a sick-as pinch and swing your heel through the exposure onto a good perch around the right side and work your self on top of that heel to top out at the most exposed part of the boulder.

I'm upgrading this. Felt by far the hardest thing I did today. It was the last thing I did today and also my beta was full on power boy beta, so take that with a grain of grain. Great line that is almost all time but some things just felt a little wonky.

Fantastic lowball. That starting hold complex is great. I found a sequence that felt significantly easier that the OG beta (at least for me) although I did it both ways to be sure. The difficulty of Adens OG beta is pretty height dependent as I was able to bump to the good sloper, avoiding a super cruxy foot move. The new school Grecian God beta is simply pull on via a left foot smear and slap that right heel next to your right hand. Removes the height dependence and softens the grade but is wonderful my dudes and dames.
Kind of a must do easy line. Seems like its a little chossy but the amazing grid of jugs gives you JTree dragon scales vibes.

The Goat Trestle is p-rad. Did the "Impossible Railroad" hike today with my brother in law and it was very nice. I do recommend. At like mile 3 plus or minus 2 there are a handful of boulders on the right side with an exoskeleton of crystal dike or something. The one closest to the railroad can be climbed easily on the right side and the features are cool enough to merit a log on 8a. Maybe I should explore the main wash of New Hueco and see if anything down there is not chossy? There absolutely HAS to be good rock somewhere around here

That was a lot of driving. Left SD at almost 11pm, slept in a rest stop shortly outside of Vegas then continued onward and got to Cabin Fever at 2:20! Woot woot! Listened to the entire "Song of Susannah" and started the final "Dark Tower" Book and I'm loving it. Thanks Mr. King for this cerebral wonderful fantasy epic! Also thanks Mr Barron for showing me this lovely rig. Saved my days climbed metric since I couldn't quite pull those titties. Rad power moves lead to tricky mantle! Foot blew on the second move on flash go. boo. Yay joes and yay friends =D.

This thing will settle in as a classic. Amazing features, well protected and such an easy approach! Great ledges and cool compressive crux. Def a tad soft for V8 but V7 seems fair. So close on the flash, but that'll happen when you forget the cigars. The downclimb is the most awkward one I have done in joes, which is the biggest downside.

This is given V2 but pretty sure it deserves an upgrade. Insanely cool features on this block. Top out is a little hard! I wanted to do 
"I like what you got" but I was showing off to Scott how dope the hand jam was by swinging back and forth when all the skin on the back left side of my hand sloughed off... it was a good one.

It was nice. I enjoyed myself. But it was quite easy. I didn't top out as far left as the line on MP had but I simply stood up on the obvious bulge hand holds and walked up (without using any "jugs") so moving any further left would have felt just silly.

I scoped the Wash Bouldres last year with Chooch and knew I wanted to get back here. Thank goodness I had fellow single boy, the one and only Mr. Dirk Irector to join me on this lovely fitness day! This climb has cleaned up a ton since I looked at it last year and the features are great and the line is inspiring.  A little like the "Hail Mary (way lake)" of Joes. That last reach is just far enough to turn caterpillars into butterflies. Ran into a super rad group of guys here. We were well met. Ka.
Hmmm... Human Music, I like it!

What a wild ride. I think me n scott are straight beat off at this point. Im a mantle machine and this tough lip encounter was indeed a tough lip encounter. I went full wild man which helped but without scotts tender loving words to guide my right foot all would have been for naught. Time to pop that Quad! And yes Scott exiting the wash to meet our nephew was a folly, but at least it was a good workout of a folly!
All aboard the struggle bus! all aboard!

I am past my Yokai Limit so this send was unbelievable. Somehow ripped a hole in my pointer with these comfy holds which makes no sense. Fun moves though. Could be 7 but soft 8 or solid 7 is fair.  Definitely a grade or two harder that Dyno Time low but not sure which climb that speaks more to.
Yessirreebobyankeedoodie! I have been reduced to a puddle of flesh. Maybe I need to do some of those new hip flesh runs. Cool Ball Ricks on this.
Cleaning up some fun easier lines now that I am a squashed banana. A glorious set of balls/knockers/knobs on this rig.  Sit start is a little meh

This must have been done by some bored lad or lass but I have yet found no information so I am dubbing it "An Ape Named Ape" until I hear otherwise. Start on Bubbatronic but from the jugs move right through a rad slot-gaston-thing making a big reach up and right to better holds. A little awk with the tiered landing/rock in the landing but that reach is a peach of a reach if you are hearin what I preach. I will put "FA" on 8a because as Jurassic Park taught us "Nobody Cares" but wouldn't dare to put "FA" on MP.

Obviously this is harder than the original... but only minutely so. 7B is what we call the "pyramid wrecker" so hard 7A Plu it is. Shoutout purple Totoro shirt getting all the compliments. Finally getting the recognition it deserves.
What a silly name. Honestly a better start than the original as it keeps the compression theme longer. The og start is just a cosmetic connection your mind mistakes for thematic. Again 7B oh so bad.
Thought it might be cool, then started thinking it was poop, then found an enjoyable sequence that was cool. We will call it cool poop. Fun working with a cumulatively exhausted Waffle.

Perfect name Kody! Getting the seconds ascent after Kody just makes it even more good. Great fun building that landing with the boys and making the slightly scary landing not scary at all. Great jugs lead to awesome feature with slightly techy top.  Ill drink to that!

Also quite wonderful. Already forgot all the names of the people I met today. Nice holds with fun moves, will clean up nicely. I think Jordan got the FA? If so ill change the name if I ever learn it has ha real one.

Worst of the bunch. Start as for the center line but move lefter through the easier more chossy holds. Not bad but not great. So funny that wince i started building my wall my outside climbing time has plummitted lol

No idea what the actual name is. Ill maybe fix it one day. This climb is the cool campus to the right of "When Life Gives You Lemons". Was originally told V8 but this thing is soft and glorious. Such a fun move. Gymtastic. I did not flash. boo. Good job shirley, first v8 flash for you? =P.
Absolutely wonderful. Thanks Daniel for the awesome bachelor party weekend. This was the perfect climb to start the day.

10 beers is too few for a handful of boys. Next time more beer. Another fake name because I just have no idea. On the direct opposite corner of "When Life Gives You Lemons". Started pretty high on a good right hand seam crimp and something opposing for the left. Got a high right foot and just slapped to a jug. Soft. Worked with with Nick. Thanks for organizing Nick!

Another one that I'm just slapping a fake name on. This is on the back side of "When Life Gives you Lemons", its that almost cool looking compression shelf thing. But don't let it fool you, its not that fun. Definitely knee bar crux, that right toe is tiny. Thanks Bryce for bringing a knee pad. Speaking of Bryce I hope your foot wasn't too fucked.  I started with the left hand on the awkward meat hook instead of the slightly lower crimp. Absolutely incredible that I managed to pull this, I guess I really just wanted to look good for Gabe! ;)

There are likely many variations on this wall but there is a ton of moss. I cleaned up enough to make the line go but I bet there are many many hidden holds still. This is the most obvious line on the slab which goes up the center with a big move to an obvious big edge.

Might be V4, has a pretty tough stand up top out move. On the obvious boulder start on the part of the rock closest to the road just below the right side of the long shelf of "Mineral King Rd."  There are some very cool edges on this rig. Luckily they run out before the crux standup. Calling this "Fire Force" as a shout out to anime, but also to the real life fire fighters (not animated) who helped protek the MK valley. Bc of their protection most of the brush surrounding this boudler was cleaned off which made it way more pleasant. As obvious as thsi boulder is I had not done it until today becuase of the annoying brush.

An obvious line I first visualized more than a decade ago. Follow the obvious right to left shelf feature by sit starting just below the right side of the shelf (same start as "Fire Force"). As all good lines go this thing is contrived and all holds above the quintessential shelf are off. Probably means there are a lot of variations but its rad.

Another one I envisioned more than a decade ago. on the left side of the boulder start relatively high on a left hand gaston and the namesake tooth hold for your right hand. That fucker has three bullet teeth which really dig in for a sweet and sticky grip. Do one move mini dyno to the lip. Cheyaah! This one DEFINITELY has lower start potential. Could be hard and good.

This is the most obvious boulder in all of MK because it is seen by anyone who has ever hiked at the Eagle-Mosquito trailhead. I would bet some of these lines have already been done but no worries. Start sitting a little akwardly near a rock in the landing to the right of the obvious ledge feature of (Mineral King Rd.). Its a pretty juggy hold. Move basically straight up through obvious good hold making a kind of tricky top out move which might use a mono.

Dubbing this boulder "Stormlight". This whole boulder is absolutely stellar. Seriously, its ludicrously good. It has probably a dozen total lines. You know this boudler is good becuase its like 3.5+ miles away and off trail but it had an anchor set up on the slab side! Damn this shit is dope. Anyway, this line is located on the steepest side of the boulder on the right side. Start sitting with a downpull crimp for your left and a right facing crimp for your right. Make an amazing big move to a crimp jug and bounce through some nice edges for a techy mantle.

Would be 5 starts but that right start hold is a little friable. sad. Left side of the steepets side of the boulder. Start compressing on arete and opposing crimp. Some interesting slaps gets you to another not gimme mantle. The perfect crimp above the lip makes it mucho enjoyablo. I cant believe how long I had to wait to finally see this boudler in person. Buddy system everyone. never forget. Worth the wait though.
Start as for Not a Woman but traverse left into "My Sun, My Moon, My Starlit Sky". Not that good really.

After getting up the infamous granite face once you start to enter the juniper trees on the final rise to the lake. Jag across eagle creek and find this rock. Start sitting on great holds low, throgh a high arcing dice into the air and land your heel right into that cup. Sploosh! Use the good heel to power straight up through a rad edge. Waaay harder than I expected. Looks maybe V2 but it put me on my ass a lot. Means is probably not V5 but it sure felt like it today.

Second ascent!!! Hell yeah Rod! This is Rods FIRST out door climb, hell, I think it was is FIRST EVER rock climb and it was an FA out in the middle of nowhere! This has to be some sort of record. Fun to hike with someone who can actually out hike me. SO proud of you for snagging this FA and stoked to see you become a bouldering nut. Also good name my dude.

Holy cow this may take the cake for best V0 in MK. Again on the left side of Eagle Creek after the granite face part of the trail. Somehow I had never looked at this boudler before but it has some of the coolest crisscrossing large quartz (or marble, what do i know im not a doctor) veins. It also has some juggy crack systems to make for a juggy good time. This is the most obvious line on the boulder starting in the center.  at the base of the crack on good holds.
Left side of the same amazing rock.
The same great rock starting on some xenos on the right.

Cannot give 5 stars because the flakes are hollow but it is dtop dead stunning.  One of the best backdrops for a boudler anywhere. and clocking in at about 18 feet this face has  a lot of climbing. ON the uphill side of the boudler start on two small crimps and make a tough-ishmove into a gaston, which puts you in to the massive flake system. Climb up via the flak to another massive edge and continue up. Try not to spam your reach and actually do a rock climbing move at the end, but since I was sans spotter on the flash FA burn I max reached to the lip. Cannot wait to get back to this boulder with the boys, both sad and non-sad alike.
Awesome xeno ladder on the Eagles crest side of the lake. Somebody must have done this already. Joey did it too! Woohoo! So fun doing this hike with Joey and Danbee!

On the Phlebotomist boulder, to the left of the tree is a short face with some cool xenos. Sit start with two of em, slap in some toe hooks out leftand derp up left hand to a gaston. Your ass swings out for a mildly entertaining thrutch.  not as easy as i expected

Start on the back right of the Knight Boulder and do some cool moves in some angled crimps until you can hit the top right arete and do a surprisingly hard rock over. I think a link up of this into Horseback Ride or vica versa could be pretty fun.

This surprised me! It's very cool and surprisingly easy compression. On the Knight boulder this is on the slot between the horse head and the adjacent boulder (back of the horse head).  Start sitting pretty low and slap up to a at cool rock over. Epona is one of my favorite fantasy horses ever so you know this climb is at least decent.

Pretty sure I tried this from the water years and years ago when the lake was full and was to scarred while wet. turns out its quite easy and quite nice, like a leisurely horseback ride. Landing is not great but climb is nice. Back left side of the Knight Boulder

I've looked at this potential line for a long time. Start as for MSMMMSS but make a huge move up and right to a Gaston. From their continue up and right through the depression in the wall. I ripped out part of the big Jug on the send go, but its still a jug so no difficulty change.
Extend the original line (My Sun, My Moon, My Starlit Sky) by starting way down and left where Less Fuzzy starts. Actually adds some cool moves and some enduro to this rad V2

On the snout side of the horse head feature, do a cool high pop up foot to get over the bulge. You can use holds on the left corner but make sure to stay on the actual horse face for full value. Landing is pretty bad with rocks and water so probably try not to fall

Requires late season when the lake is mostly dry because this boulder is mostly underwater. Once its dry enough there is an awesome flat landing for this incredible looking feature. It literally looks like a horse head or a knight chess piece. Start in the center of the face and go up and left through the honker xeno. A little tall but its so good. Tried years ago in hiking shoes and no pads, but with actual shoes its casual and fun!
Same difficulty as the better line. Start in the same spot but instead of going to the glorious xeno, go right over the horse head.

When there is water in the lake there is a pretty obvious big rock that essentially makes an Island. Not to be confused with the actual island further in the lake. There is a channel between the main split boulder and the flat topped boulder it leans on. If you start in the center of the channel and climb the flat topped boulder, you will have climbed this. When the lake is full this is completely underwater so must be done later in the season.
Of the underwaters, this is definitely the best. Big ol' holds, non wet landing and easy.

Start on the right side of the boulder and traverse left (through the start of 'Underwater') until you go far enough. Then top out  guess. Meh. I think there was a kinda hard move at the start but its been like 6 months so maybe v2? maybe easier? Who knows, this will probably never be done again so who really cares. ME thats who.

On the same higher tier as "Sex, Shower, and Hiking" at Mosquito 5 toward Eagle is this wall which has a cool reverse "N" system of cracks. Cyrillic has a backwards N in its alphabet hence the name. This line is the diagonal up and right line. Quite nice jugs, some smeary feet at the bottom but a good line. Might be V0.
On the Cyrillic N this is going straight up the left vertical crack. Might also be V0 cannot remember, its been too long. Good holds make it enjoyable.

Toward the north west side of Lake 2 there were a few small boulders. I hopped on this one that was a small boulder with a small freestanding roof. There were two crimps beneath the roof with yields a cool move to the lip and a decent lip encounter.

Shoutout to Beyrlsofcash with this name. Probably the coolest line on the Cyrillic boulder, sit start the right side of the reverse N system. Some nice lie backing leads to a few crux options. Nice and fun, good job Beyrlsofchache for figuring out the beta even with a tired body. Meow!

Dyno from a large hold to another large hold. Also at the same north west side of Mosquito 2 near a large felled dead Western Juniper. Did it with one shoe and a sock bc my other shoe was needed to film

Obvious splitter crack by where we camped at Mosquito 5. Its on one of the slightly higher tiers toward eagle lake. Starts hands, to fists then slightly off width for the finish although I lie backed the end. Named for a silly answer to "when should I be naked?". lol. Because this is a crack i feel like its likely someone else has done it but oh well.

On the same higher tier toward eagle is an amazing warm up wall with tons of variations and good holds / cracks throughout! I did 6 distinct vertical lines up this wall which is about 30 feet wide and ~11 feet tall on the left and ~ 8 feet tall on the right. Im going to just name these all 1-6 so bear with me. This one is pretty far left starting on a left facing edge/flake feature and going straight up.
To the right of the aforementioned left facing edge/flake, and to the left of the most obvious vertical crack. Start on a crimpy dish at about chest height and go up
Best of the lines on this wall. Go up the most obvious of the vertical cracks. Sit start
Sit start on a crack basically in the center of the wall. Right facing crack and some balance leads you to the top.
Stand start on a crack at about the right third of the boulder. Climb
Stand start another crack pretty far right on the boulder (but before the crack with plants in it)

Could be V2 but its pretty exploratory. So many cool features making for a fantastic warmup. This wall is just less the vertical so really lets you warm up those fingers and feet. If you do it twice in a row I guarantee you will use different holds.

Honestly this traverse is pretty rad. Cooler than the left to right because it finishes on the taller part of the boulder. Again awesome features on this pretty long 30ft traverse. Cool this way too bc the is crux is at the end.

A decent slightly delicate face compression thing to the left of Pangolin. Start to the left of pangolin standing on opposing holds. The first move smearing to get the foot up is probably the crux, but  its a bit delicate after that so good foot placement/trust is needed. Stay to the left of the arching Pangolin sloper feature finishing just to the right of the downclimb. Not great but it is one more okay climb in this relatively dense woodson area!
Wonderful crimps on this little guy. WIll certaintly add thsi to my South Slope warm up circuit. It faces north too which is great for avoiding some son!
Meh. Pull off the ground felt very hard then that was it. The right hand holds are pretty cool but its short and feet are meh and rock quality on left is meh.

It was decently hot today but starting on BOTH crimps under the roof seemed impossible. I started sitting with right hand on the obvious crimp and left hand opposing on the lip. First move was a hard hand heel match then the fun part starts! Surprisingly fun little compression guy with an odd top! Poor berylsofcash getting heat exhaustion: LR hits hard with the heat + sun sometimes. Definitely one of the toughest hikes out ever carrying as much as i can and rationing water! Newtopia cider afterward to celebrate being alive! My shoulders hurt.

No idea how I pulled this today, an it felt easy to boot! I think its one of those climbs where it gets disproportionately harder the more times you try. That hold will always be too sharp, but that's what makes it so rad. Locking off was too hard so just a big ol DP to that glorious dike pinch. A true lock off would b coo too. Sorry berylsofcash for trying to kill you in the heat today =P. 85 is monstrous at LR

Holy crowley that was close. Was tryna send fast to support berylsofcash on Shortness of Breath and I got myself mega flash pumped trying hard beta mid climb. I thought I saw the line but I was up there like... dang this doesn't work! lolz. Had to audible and only my incredible thigh squeeze power got me to the top. I cant even remember what I did but I did it, I remember that.
Def not V8 but some cool moves, to some jug choss, to a nice top out.

Incredible hard to discern where this thing was intended to go. Seem smost natural to trend right toward the top? Ill take it. Difficulty is pretty dubious too, harder than it looks. Heel toe cam is pcool.

Weekend in Mammoth with the Bae berylsofcash! Its the Margarita Festival, we pulled!! Anyway, my 2015 Ford Focus could not make it to Hartley... popped tire on an attempt. Had to put the spare on, somehow turn around and navigate back down. Spare is flat now too. Lets climb! Hike ain't too bad from the Freeway. We got as lucky as ducks get by running into those rad dudes of whom I have forgotten all their names. They not only drove Me and Mary Ann and our pads down but gave be a beer and pumpe dup my spare! I owe you big. Oh this climb is nice.
yes, its fun.
Fun, this is.
Drink all the beers. This thing has cool features.
It's NOT easy for people like us (wet people that is).
Fun bouldering so close to your house!!! How rad Mr Girth and Mrs Waffle! Left or right?! I don't even remember but I know it was important
He and She did the stand as warm up. (I did not)
Start as for "Nightcrawler" but immediately exit right  after the first right hand bump, directly over your starting heel

My beta feels broken, hence the V7. Mr Girth on the other hand is just a dick. I had no chance of doing it the way everyone else does. These sweaty sausages on that angled crimp! in the direct sun! no way hose!! Props to the human waffle for throwing herself a this thing like a thing that gets thrown. I just hit a small directional crimp then spanned all the way to the good hold
Pfun. Plittle, pshort but pfun. Chilling with my beryls of cash!
Start as per Finish Your Dinner but don't go right at all.  Hit the lip match and mantle. Tough with the tree at your back. Well Tough or dumb, one of the two.
Where did Kody fall on this!?
Static version better than OG.
Looks like is should be cake but then it ain't. Tricky slippery top.

Don't know if this is the correct name. I think maybe it's the stand to Spicy Beaver? Anyway far right line on Darkside Boulder. Decent little guy. I need the V Points to break my 75 point record from 8 years ago. All i gotta do is snag the Choadler and im good to go.... he said.

I did this wonky, whats new? Speaking of being surrounded by fish, this is my second time to Pine Mountain and last time I came with the lovely Andrew and the lovely Drea. That was literally like 8 years ago!!! (10-03-2016). Those same fish swam with me today! How cool right!?
Hard to grade but yes that press is pretty pure. Gunning for that V point record from last time! Last time I was here was October 3rd, 2016 and I whipped up 75 V Points.
The Choadler is harder. Change my mind.
Those features got me wet. Well actually I'm always wet because apparently I am a greasing god. What an honor.
That was some ludicrous beta I used. Seriously one of the oddest sequences ive ever done. There was a press cross, an intentional knee push. Odditys for sure, but entertaining
Short but enjoyable, sit looks like it could be cool. Meeting the frolf boys at Pono! Classic. Chase should have come for that open mike!
Rad slopers, but that first move seemed real not fun. That akward landing rock makes pulling on meh. After teh first move tho it was my bread butter and toaster.
Cool to finally check out castle! This climb was nice.
Tried to use static beta, I should have known jumping to jugs was the way! Great line.
This this was nice.
Cool Jergs but movement felt a little odd. Did stand and sit. sit is better.

Nothing like a good ol' one-of-anything to change a weekend in bishop with my honey to a friendsgiving in the bay with the sandbox. Good thing he flashed that thing years ago  at the Cliffs of Id; A lot of frolf would not have been had otherwise. A great use of a one of anything. Dela, Beer, GGP, Winery Frolf, Friends, Beer Die, Homer, good thigs. Thanks nate! Also shoutout Banka for being rad.
Def a unique and fun line. Nice to get on after the crowds went home
Zat vas Paumpy! Very nice climb with satisfying top moves. Did stand and sit. Our boys b frolfing today.
Almost did not flash! Kind of a hard single move, but its a good one! Don't really like climbing with other people anymore lawlz
I found many hard ways to to the throw to the lip. I rock. Very cool long line with awesome knockers at the beginning. Good thing I b good at  mantling.

I don't think I am allowed to take flash for this, I did Mr Witty a decade ago, but I did do it first burn today and i was very proud of myself so i am taking it. My cold tips actually didn't feel wet. Thank god I did it in one go otherwise it would have never happened. THanks scott for remembering mono. Now i can finally project Less Poetry Please!
Good mantle and fun low move. Maybe I should restart my lost ambition to check everything V7 and under in the tablelands?
Nice jergs. Way to go honey on Serengetti!!

This is a big shoutout to Scott. Without me he would never have tried this thing, but likewise, without him I would have never sent. We complete each other. I doubt this was still an undone project but as of the new guidebook it was still listed as a project "Erik's Arete" in sleepy hollow. Crazy triple bump big span radness. Also small shoutout to our own Erik with a K, and also fishbowl. If Scott truly got the FA I got the second, but who cares anyway, its only a model.

Gobble Gobble is three stars! True that fish bowl. Recommending this because the rock is bullet and the moves are fun. Also because I had such a good time in this wannabe ice caves with Scott, Mary Ann and Erik (not with a c). You guys all rock. In the book this has a comma.

Oooohh Whee hes's crimping! Crimping real hard! Great to see E-Rock and climb silly obscure things with him and Scott. Loving my uncanny ability to get people to try things lol! Speaking of obscure, this climb is amazing. I think I cheated and started a little too high, but this climb is cool as nails and hard as nails. Highly recommend for you slab folks.
This is way better than zero stars! Especially since the turtle head protruding feature is so cool the wall begs to be climbed. Was fun mantling in that dihedral in my cruisers.
I think I may have actually don't Pirates Booty V4 and called it Tim's Obscurity V7. Hard to tell with the terrible descriptions but the new guide moved the number so we will just fix it in post.
I love getting Woo to do things.

Not gonna lie Crabs on My Nipples took a lot out of me. Darn Crustaceans! Good session here with Erik-undercling-ripper-mcgee, Rick, Woo and Banka. Movement wise quite nice. That starting hold is rad.... but friable. That last go took all my mustard so I'm glad it went.

Since most of us don't climb V13, or even V11.. wait a second am I now in the minority? Do most people climb V11 now? Damn I'm weak. Anyway I started this 8 foot boulder 7 feet up and took 8 full points for it. Funner than expected, Choss knew I love silly climbing like this. Started spanned with pad stack between left hand sloper and the black knob.
Not as good as Raggedy Ann but very fun and the landing is flat. These climbs should have chalk more often! Fight that barn door boys and girls!

Believe it or not this was favorite climb from the trip. Its such a good lip traverse that I'm really sad its not closer to the main area or at least another well known boulder. This send kind of sums up the trip: obscure boulders that are rad, amazing friends, complete exhaustion, beer. Good times. Thank you Drew for making this trip possible and thank you everyone who was present!

How is this thing not more done!? So good. The trav is a little silly but the meat of this climb is perfect. A big move from cool crimps to a bonafide JERG. Landing is a little bad but with a few pads its very safe. I love this type of beautiful DP.

This felt like a miracle. Scott and I started right hand good right facing sidepull and left hand a crappier opposing left hand sidepull out left which is NOT how Andy Liu did it. Its harder this way and I think better. You get an awesome drop knee. So proud of Woo for breaking his rest day to try this with us. Very painful. Got em!!!
Book has this at V1 and its pretty nice so I say thats fine. Whatevs. Ill be back for shite arete!
Cool start holds fun mantle! I wanted to deo everything on this boulder but no star climbs at JTree can be so hard!
enjoyable. Rich enjoyed this one too. Speaking or Rich and fat, we did the Great Chasm which was pretty fun! The "coffin" isn't that hard and would recommend as a quick climbing detour

Another one that the sister rocked. A little spicy up high but I knew once she was up there she would nail it! This little close area has some good easy stuff! Speaking of Hot and Juicy, I almost got the ultra classic Streetcar Lie Down start! Next time for sure.

Amazing visit from the sister and her Alaska family! We got her on waves and up rocks!! Send train with me rich and Karen! A little tall for years off the couch but my sister rocked it!. Can you believe this was my parents FIRST time to Joshua Tree. I cannot. Pops said his favorite part was climbing! We got the legend Jack Vasko to scramble. It was loot my dudes. The nephews were a blast too, glad I brought that Maya Flya! Pokemon Go forever.
Tried first go in cruisers. No go. This be good tho. In the book this is 5a and it has a hyphen not a space "Semi-Precious"

Start chest height on a bunch of choss to the right of Mr Long arm in that crevice. Move left through the cool ledge and wrap all the way around the detaching block instead of going up. Not terrible but definitely not good.

Probably not a FA either but I am a troll here so

Same start as Mr. Longarm for off rout the entire rail. Go left instead with a decent shoulder move in the the detaching block. Wrap around left and finish that way. Not as good as the OG but def worth doing if at this boulder.

Unlikely an FA, but will still log on 8a as such.

If someone gets mega inspired and actually digs out the landing this might actually be pretty cool, but currently its one of those lie down starts where you are so close to the ground that you cannot actually tell if you are climbing or not. Start beneath the OG holds literally less than a foot off the ground. Move into the OG start holds then do the normal climb. 

Probably not an FA either.

Probs V8, but that means poison control is probs v7. Oh wells. Shark tooth is still hard. 

That dank dust is dank!! Oh yeah good job marina on that thing over there.

Oh yeah also happy bday to the one and only chaseypoo. Glad to play more frolf this weekend than bouldering lolol. Good times
Middle finger was the better choice.

Is my home wall helping me crimp!! I do love those escape dot crimps. 

I remember years ago chase telling me how easy this was so i was too embarressed to even try. Knowing food was inevitable =P. Today i somehow flashed. wowzers
I can actually climb? What a miracle. Good times on obscure goodies with chase scott and the crew.
Rad warmup. Good height.
Cool. Feet are worse than they look. Other Scott bringing some weird juju. That gummy work toss was hilarious.
Blew the flash bc i didn't realize there was a stand start and I dropped off from the top jug lolol. Some of those holds feel bad, and only get worse with more and more sun + sweat
If you got the span, the stand start is the crux. Cool extension on an already cool climb. Michelle stoked that you and Luna made it out for some great camaraderie.
That was not nice and easy. Start is rad top is meh. Was hoping this would be cool so I could recommend it to others but alas I could not do that. Shoutout glove climbing and the Little Arete V4
Def a softie but its very fun. Good second go train with Mr. Girth. Both of us missing the big first move on the flash.

I actually have some really normal dreams. Well maybe because they are so normal they are abnormal. I mean I dream about doing yardwork: pulling weeds, mowing the lawn, trimming the trees, digging holes; that sort of stuff. Best part is usually when I wake up I get to do it again, but better this time since I've already done it once. This climb was fun, good working with the davids, and chase. Happy birthday chase.

Based on Scotts star algorithm this would be 5/5 stars. (1) Height/landing, (2) Aesthetic, (3) Movement, (4) rock quality. (5) Pureness. Well i guess MP says there is a V8 right exit so maybe 4.5 stars, losing half a star on pureness. But like Toad I award it the happening half start since I could do it and Scott couldn't. boo yah! Home wall doing me good on the crimpers!
Not fully warm yet and this felt nails, i say NAILS! Get me a hammer bc this was NAILS. honestly probs a softy, but still a goody. Many sweet grips.

Definitely a must do of the area. I'm falling back on Scotts star mechanism but is very pragmatic which is nice: (1) Height/landing - landing is a little awk, but its safe. Still earns star.  (2) meh aesthetic, so it does not earn this star (3) movement (4) rock quality (5) pureness. So I guess 4 stars (like I logged). Different beta than Scott but yeah, I'm a different human: believe it or not. Almost snagged the sit but I'm a tired boy. Def not V9.

Holy fuck Triassic is way better than advertised. Maybe that's intentional? Anyway I did nor realize I was saying
