"Cretaceous" incorrectly for God knows how long. Actually God doesn't know, why would he pay attention to that? Also doe he even exist? Anyway, south-ish from Cretaceous there is a corridor with a face that has two rad opposing slopers with bit rail at the bottom. I did that. I did that to add to the confusion. Your Welcome. Start right hand flexy hold left hand pressing on said rail.

The top of this thing is scary! You got pinball potential and the top jug is a chicken head! Anyway, if you are reading this you probably read my stand start FA. For 2 extra points start on the rail with a high heel and pull up to the flexy hold. Awesome feature, if landing was better this for sure would have been done by OG trolls.

First flash on this bad boy! I'm a proud boy. Also I really though Scott was spotting me for the mantle. Turns out he wasn't. he just poked his head over from Thump to watch. I heard his voice and was instantly reassured. I must say, my trust in you is big time because I fucking did the mantle.

Top is a sandbox. Toe hook beta is fun but not necessary. The half rotation campus in was easier. But this climb is about being memorable and hell yeah it was memorable. Pinch epicing was also memorable. Nice.
A perfect warm up. Remember pull out not down. Don't be a duchebag. Oh i did this barefoot for no apparent reason but it was nice

Scott makin MOVES on Trents mom. PLURAL. That climb is way funnier when you know a Trent. Anyway, the grips on this are all time! Movement too! A tad contrived but it is fun as fuck and aesthetic as fuck. First climb in my live using both a ladder and a rope and let me tell you... it helps immensely! Seriously saves SO much energy. So awesome. Good climb.
Multiple years in the making. So much fun this boy. No single move is harder than V5 but damn that's a lot of moves for a boulderer. Good times with Ned and nick.

Awesome climb with sweet grips as the MP says. Good ol' steep roof with jugs leading to sweet as compressive crux! Felt something pop in my knee on the flash, had my right heel in that big hueco for the first hard right hand slap before the lip. It wasn't loud though so I think that means nothing tore. Definitely wont right heel for a while but luckily the one I really want this trip "The Beautiful Boobies" AKA "Playmate of the Year" can be doen without a right heel. May have been too cold at 9 am by the river to warm up here. Oh well, full sweep on this with the boyz

Tired boyz. Failed on Playmate of the year again. 3rd day on but feels more like 4th day bc day 0 was like 10 hours of shoveling snow and post holing. Got to the blind throw on the flash go and thought maybe this was soft, then proceeded to not be able to do multiple moves for a long while. Finally pieced together the puzzle with Ned and Nick and took her to the top. Fattys for dinner was  nice! GPT4 gonna take our jobs!

Movement masterpiece. Sit start feels a little forced, but it does set up that amazing Gaston sequence. So many good moves. I love that this climb feels like its slowly decreases difficulty over the course of the climb which is super rad bc you are getting more tired but its getting easier. I wonder how much work the FAers did to excavate this rig. Cicadas do burrow underground so maybe the name is a reference to that. First move of White Buffalo is so frustrating.

Too cold. I did not enjoy being this cold. If only that left hand crimp was a better hold this would be an All Star ~V4. As is its a good V3 with one hard move. Still cool. I realized that whole under cling feature is glued / cemented which makes sense I guess, but still loses some purity. The Flu area is pretty coo! Shout Ned for his impeccable form on the top of this!
I am so tired. Wrecked really. Cleaning boulders really should not count as a rest day. Good end to the day to really put a fork in my ass. Fun climbing.

Three dimensional climbing at its finest. Seriously so rad. Those starting tufas are in-creh-dah-blay! Pretty sure I would have flashed if it was not 22 degrees out. Impossible to warm up and impossible to stay warm for more than like 2 moves. The rock is a really big ice cube. On the flash I stopped feeling my hands on the third move and kept climbing but eventually I grabbed a hold wrong but could not tell. Shoutout Pinch for validating his trip with this one, and shoutout Ned for finishing the epic with a send!

This boulder may now be my favorite right fork warm up area. This and midget give a great variety of holds and movement to get warm. The next generation link up of Dustbuster into Midget and back into Dustbuster while eliminating all the big holds is the perfect end to a warm up.
This has a standalone boobie which is nice.

I think I've tried this thing every trip to goes. Multiple sessions last year and the year before that. So stoked to finally put it down, and pretty darn cleanly I must say. So may bodily pains in my body, and many butterflies in my basked but pulled boys. Extruded even. I feel like a million Buckaroonies!!
Flashed so obviously cannot be V9. Very cool moves. That Chat crew was pretty entertaining. I wonder what sort of weird things they said about us afterward lol. I can be quite a raging eccentric.
Props to Ned on completing a rad 7-7-7!! Nice work. This climb is pretty rad! Unique and fun. Nice hanging with Hal!!
I feel like 2 million Buckaroonies!!!
Damn that shit was dope. Feels so unlike Joes, but in a wonderful kind of way. Great slabbing this one with ultra satisfying finish.

Close last year, felt good to clean her up. Everyone should get on the sweet right exit "An Ape name Ape". It was way too cold again. 22 degrees when we got back to the cars... and the wind was wipping... its too much. Good quick evening session with Ned after his super fun meetings. The quick sesh meant we got to snag a nice Fattys with our boy Scotticus
A little friable and a sandbox at the top but a pretty good warm up with juggos.
Honestly a decently cool move from the good incut slot to the lip... but either I started wrong or this is V3. I will likely do again if warming up at Pimpin Jeans so thats a plus.
Huh. I guess this is a climb.

Handful of gos. Had to try pretty hard on this boy. Thought I might finally be strong enough to cruise, but no, we are not at cruising altitude my dudes and dames, we are not. Fun climb and with good company to boot! Also shoutout Ned for making his argument for one of the best last days in joes by pulling Gurkha AND Point Break. Fantastic last day of a fantastic trip! Drive safe!

Almost guaranteed not to be an FA but ill take those coveted 8a points until someone corrects me. An easier sequence could drop the grade to V8 probs but whatever. Start as For Cretaceous Sit, but after the first move hitting the big undercling move left utilizing another small undercling to lunge out left to a cool pinch block on the left arete. Paste a foot on and jump to the perpetually dirty crack jug and swing away dear boys.

My goal this year is 10 V10s and my first V11 (time to mega proj fight club).  With this tick I have my first soft V10 of 2023, woot woot! Second session. Was gonna give up but the weather took a turn for the worse so Scott gave up on climbing for the day (he yoyo-ed alot today) and suggested we take a nice walk to look at boulders. We found the Bad but couldn't find anything in golden ladle. Anyway with a physical and mental break I came back primed and proper. With a subtle foot beta change early I took this down using one of the most aggressive and loud slaps I have made to date. Cant wait to use that sound bye in a remix at some point. Thanks scott for filming until the end. Gold. Soft.

This deserves the upgrade. Granted Scott and I are tired and its too cold outside to actually properly fuel your muscles but dang that was a lot. Had to try so so hard. Why is it snowing again? At least the little ponds are freezing over to make beautiful, thin and clear ice porcelain sheets! I cant believe how happy those ices made me.

I know you aren't supposed to log stands that were not established by the FA-ers but I had trouble reading the Eon Red description and this looked fun and easier that Eon Blue. Cool Knee bar makes it worth adding an easier start I think. Fourth day on, so squeezing in a tiny bit more climbing and now looking forward to 2 rest days =D.
This deserves the hype. Very nice. Crux reach feels decently hard for V1 but wonderful holds and movement leave a delectable taste in the mouth hole. Finally some sunny nice weather!

This should probably not be V0. Find a V0 climber who can do this and ill show you a unicorn. This is the awesome multi ledge feature on the backside of "Golden" which features a mid  climb mantle! Pretty freaking rad. Scott epic-ing on the "stand up" post mantle part. lololol. Very fun and not scary despite MPs PG13 distinction
